(1, 33, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.01', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/01-General/GeneralHome.html', 'Vendors.General Information', 'Vendors - General Information', 'Vendors - General Information     Vendors - General Information This section covers the activites realted to your vendors. Accounts -  Purchase Orders -  Quotes -  Purchases -  Payments -  POP -  Credit Memos -  Vendor Status -'),
(2, 6, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.02.01', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/02-Accounts/01-NewAccount.html', 'Vendor Account.Entering', 'Entering a Vendor Account', 'Entering a Vendor Account\r \r \r \r \r  Entering a Vendor Account \r Vendor accounts include any outside organization that you acquire goods or services from. Generally, they are organizations that you make payments to. \r NOTE: Vendor accounts may be created at time of purchase by entering the required information and checking the Add/Update button in the Purchase/Receive, Payment or Purchase Order form. In this case, an unique account ID must be entered and the account will be created using the standard terms, default Purchase GL account, no User ID, Account Number, Federal ID number, or additional shipping or billing addresses. \r To create a new account:\r \r   Select Vendors-&gt;New Vendor or Select the New icon form the Vendors-&gt;Maintain Vendors page.\r    Enter an unique Vendor ID. The Vendor ID (or short name) is an unique field to identify this vendor form all other vendors. Maximum length is 20 characters.\r   Enter remaining Primary Contact  and Main Mailing (billing) Address information. Required fields are identified by a (*).\r   Enter the default purchase account. This is typically an accounts payable general ledger account type.\r   Enter an user id assigned to this vendor. \r   Enter your account number with this vendor. This number can be used for purchase orders, checks to reference your account to the vendor.\r    Enter the Tax or Federal ID number. generally used for tax purposes.\r    If the vendor can ship from multiple locations, additional ship from addresses can be added in the Shipping Addresses form area. Unlimited shipping addresses may be assigned to a vendor but only one may be added at a time.\r   Enter the payment terms you have with the vendor. The defaults are preloaded but may be over-ridden on a vendor by vendor basis. \r   If the vendor has additional remit to (billing) addresses, they may be added in the Billing Addresses form area. Unlimited billing addresses may be assigned to a vendor but only one may be added at a time. \r   Press the Save icon and the record will be saved and you will be returned to the Maintain Vendors page. \r \r Related Topics\r Vendors\r   Updating a vendor account\r   Deleting a vendor account\r Setting up a vendor credit limit\r Purchase Orders\r Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Purchase/Receive Inventory \r Receiving items from a purchase order\r Reports and Forms \r   Checking vendor balances'),
(3, 6, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.02.02', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/02-Accounts/02-EditAccount.html', 'Vendor Account.Editing', 'Editing a Vendor Account', 'Editing a Vendor Account\r \r \r \r \r Editing a Vendor Account\r To edit a vendor record:\r \r   Select Vendors-&gt;Maintain Vendors page.\r   Select the Edit icon next to the vendor to edit. A search box has been provided to quickly locate the vendor.\r   Edit/update/change any fields for the vendor.\r   Add/Delete any additional shipping or billing addresses.\r   Press the Save button to save the changes. You will be returned to the Maintain Vendors page. \r \r Related Topics\r Vendors\r  Adding a new vendor account \r   Deleting a vendor account \r Setting up a vendor credit limit\r Purchase Orders\r Entering  a purchase order\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Reports and Forms \r Checking vendor balances\r \r &nbsp;'),
(4, 6, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.02.03', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/02-Accounts/03-DeleteAccount.html', 'Vendor Account.Deleting', 'Deleting a Vendor Account', 'Deleting a Vendor Account\r \r \r \r \r  Deleting a Vendor Account \r NOTE: Vendors cannot be deleted if they have a journal entry associated with them. \r To delete a vendor record:\r \r   Select Vendors-&gt;Maintain Vendors page.\r   Select the Delete icon next to the vendor to delete. A search box has been provided to quickly locate the vendor.\r   Confirm the deletion and you will be returned to the Maintain Vendors page. \r \r Related Topics\r Vendors\r  Adding a new vendor account \r Editing a vendor account \r Purchase Orders\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Reports and Forms \r Checking vendor balances\r \r &nbsp;'),
(5, 6, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.02.04', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/02-Accounts/04-PaymentTerms.html', 'Vendor Accounts.Payment Terms', 'Vendor Payment Terms', 'Vendor Payment Terms\r \r \r \r \r Vendor Payment Terms\r Vendor payment terms may be set up through the configuration screen. The terms set up will be applied as the default terms for all new vendor accounts. Additionally, existing accounts with out terms defined (or ''Use Standard Terms'') will track the terms defined in the configuration setup definitions. Individual vendor terms may also be set up for vendors whose terms are different from the standard terms. Terms may also be set up for specific purchases through the Purchase Order/Purchase procedure. \r Setting up Default Terms \r \r   Select Company-&gt;Vendor Defaults.\r   Edit the fields as necessary. The terms type defaults to the standard X% discount in Y days, Net Z days.\r   Set the default vendor credit limit to use. \r \r Setting up Vendor Specific Payment Terms\r \r    Select  Vendors-&gt;Maintain Vendors. \r   Search for the vendor whose terms you want to change and press the edit icon to reach the detailed page.\r    Under the section titled Payment Terms, check the radio button for the terms type to apply to this vendor.\r   Depending on the terms type selected, the Discount, Due In, Net and date fields will be active. Fill in the fields for the terms type selected.\r   Enter the credit limit for the current vendor.\r   Press the Save icon to save the changes.\r \r Setting Payment Terms for a Single Purchase\r \r   Select Vendors-&gt;Purchase/Receive (or Purchase Order, Vendor Quote).\r   On the form select the Open icon next to the terms field. A popup window will open with the current terms selected.\r   Change the terms as necessary and press Save to enter the new terms into the form.\r \r Related Topics\r Vendors\r  Adding a new vendor account\r Editing a vendor account\r Purchase Orders\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Reports and Forms \r Checking vendor balance\r &nbsp;'),
(6, 33, '0', 'en_us', '07.02.02', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/02-Accounts/AccountsHome.html', 'Vendors.Accounts', 'Vendors - Accounts', 'Vendors - Accounts\r \r \r \r \r Vendors - Accounts \r Vendor accounts contain information about your suppliers of inventory, services and other purchases required for your business. The procedures to setup, edit and delete vendor accounts is similar to that for customers within SmartBooks. \r Vendor Account features:\r \r   Default global settings for purchase account and terms; customizable for each individual vendor\r   Unlimited billing addresses\r   Unlimited shipping addresses\r    Individual purchase rep default assignment \r   Free-form notes field \r \r Related Topics\r Vendors\r Entering a new vendor \r Updating vendor information\r Deleting a vendor \r Setting vendor payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase  Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r   Receiving inventory directly from a vendor\r Other Vendor Actions \r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r   Writing a check to a vendor\r   Issuing a vendor credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking vendor balance\r &nbsp;'),
