(11, 33, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.02', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/02-Contacts/ContactsHome.html', 'Vendors.Contacts', 'Vendors - Contacts', 'Vendors - Contacts\r \r \r \r \r Vendors - Contacts \r Vendor contacts contain information about your suppliers of inventory, services and other purchases required for your business. The procedures to setup, edit and delete vendor contacts is similar to that for customers within SmartBooks. \r Vendor Account features:\r \r   Default global settings for purchase account and terms; customizable  for each individual vendor\r   Unlimited billing addresses\r   Unlimited shipping addresses\r    Individaul purchase rep default assignment \r   Freee-form notes field \r \r Related Topics\r Vendors\r Entering a new vendor \r Updating vendor information\r Deleting a vendor \r Setting vendor payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase  Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r   Receiving inventory directly from a vendor\r Other Vendor Actions \r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r   Writing a check to a vendor\r   Issuing a vendor credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking vendor balance\r &nbsp;'),
(12, 17, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.03.01', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/03-PurchaseOrders/01-EnterPO.html', 'Purchase Orders.Entering', 'Entering Customer Purchase Orders', 'Entering Customer Purchase Orders\r \r \r \r \r  Entering Vendor Purchase Orders\r Purchase orders are used to enter purchase from a vendor. Reports can be generated to list the inventory shortfalls and inventory purchases. Each inventory item has a minimum balance field that can be used to help identify when inventory needs to be ordered. Purchase orders do not affect your financial situation, income statement or balance sheet. they merely act as a placeholder to determine inventory stock levels needed to add or replace inventory stock levels. \r \r   From the Vendors Menu, select Purchase Orders. The Purchase Order form will load.\r   Enter the Vendor ID and click on the open icon right of the Vendor ID window. The vendor popup window will appear. Select the vendor from the list and the information will be pre-loaded into the Purchase Order form.\r     \r     NOTE: The Vendor ID text box also acts as a search box to quickly find vendors.\r     \r     Vendor records consist of a main address, billing addresses and shipping addresses. Select the billing address and shipping address from the pull down menus. New addresses may be added to either the shipping or billing address if they cannot be found from either of the menus. Selecting the add/update button will update the database whereas leaving it unchecked will just retain the address for this purchase order.\r     Drop Ship - If this is a drop ship, select the Drop Ship box and the drop ship search box will appear. Customers can be searched and their shipping information will be entered into the drop down or the shipping address may be entered directly into the address fields. \r   Enter the purchase order Post Date and expected Receipt Date. Popup calendars are provided to help with the selection.\r    Purchase Order Number - Enter the purchase order number. If left blank, the next sequential purchase order number will be automatically generated by the system.\r    Enter the your purchase reference   number, store id and purchase representative. The default accounts payable account is loaded and can be changed. The vendor payment terms are loaded when a vendor is selected from the vendor popup. If a new vendor is entered, the default payment terms are loaded. To change the payment terms, click on the icon next to the terms text field and the terms popup will be displayed. Select the terms for this purchase order and press Save to enter the terms into the purchase order form.\r   Enter the inventory items for the purchase order. The form defaults with a single inventory line but more may be added by pressing the Add button located in the lower left area of the purchase order form. Enter the quantity requested. The item cost value assigned to the sku will be placed in the price field and the line total will be calculated. \r     \r     NOTE: The inventory SKU field also acts as a search field for the inventory popup. To quickly find an inventory item, enter part of the item sku or description and press the icon next to the SKU. The SKU, description and pricing fields will be filled in. \r     \r   Enter the inventory SKU, description and price (or retrieve from the inventory popup) for the line item. Enter more line items as necessary. \r   Enter the shipping charges (or use the shipping estimator to calculate freight charges).\r   Select  the tax authority, the tax will be automatically calculated.\r   Save or Print the purchase order. Error checking will be performed and any errors will be indicated either in a popup for errors before the form is submitted or at the top of the reloaded page (for errors during  processing). If the Purchase Order number field was left blank, a number will be assigned by the system. If the Print button was selected, the purchase order will be posted first followed by a popup window displaying the possible forms to print, select the form to print and press the Print button. \r \r Related Topics\r Vendor Accounts\r Entering a new vendor \r     Editing a vendor account \r     Deleting a vendor account\r     Setting vendor payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase Orders\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a vendor\r Other Vendor Actions \r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r   Writing a check to a vendor.\r   Issuing a vendor credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking vendor balances\r Tax Authorities \r Setting up tax authorities\r    Setting up tax rates\r Shipping Estimator\r Setting up the shipping estimator'),
(13, 17, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.03.02', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/03-PurchaseOrders/02-EditPO.html', 'Purchase Orders.Editing', 'Editing a Vendor Purchase Order', 'Editing a Vendor Purchase Order\r \r \r \r \r Editing a Vendor Purchase Order\r Purchase  orders can only be edited if no items have been received from the purchase order. If any items have been received, the corresponding purchase/receipt must be removed before the purchase order can be edited. In this case, the purchase order should be closed. See Closing a Purchase Order. Closing a purchase order will remove all remaining ''quantity on  order'' quantities from inventory. \r \r   From the Vendors Menu, select Purchase Orders. The Purchase Order form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the purchase orders for the current period. Select the sales order to be edited and the sales order form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired purchase order. \r   \r   Make any necessary changes. Item rows may not be changed if some or all have been received.\r   Press the Save button to save the changes.\r \r When a purchase order is saves, the journal entry is re-posted to the database and the quantity on  order values are readjusted. This action will not affect the income statement or balance sheet since a purchase order represents an allocation of inventory and not an actual purchase (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Vendor Accounts\r Entering a new vendor \r     Editing a vendor account \r     Deleting a vendor account\r     Setting vendor payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a vendor\r Other Vendor Actions \r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r  Writing a check to a vendor\r   Issuing a vendor credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking vendor balances\r Tax Authorities \r Setting up tax authorities\r    Setting up tax rates\r Shipping Estimator\r Setting up the shipping estimator'),
(14, 17, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.03.03', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/03-PurchaseOrders/03-DeletePO.html', 'Purchase Orders.Deleting', 'Deleting a Customer Purchase Order', 'Deleting a Customer Purchase Order\r \r \r \r \r  Deleting a Vendor Purchase Order\r Purchase  orders can only be deleted if no items have been received from the purchase order. If any items have been received, the corresponding purchase/receipt must be removed before the purchase order can be deleted. In this case, the purchase order should be closed. See Closing a Purchase Order. Closing a purchase order will remove all remaining ''quantity on  order'' quantities from inventory. \r \r   From the Vendors Menu, select Purchase Orders. The Purchase Order form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the purchase orders for the current period. Select the sales order to be deleted and the sales order form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired purchase order. \r   \r   Press the Delete button and confirm the action on the confirmation popup.\r \r When a purchase order is deleted, the journal entry is removed from the database and the quantity on  order values are readjusted. This action will not affect the income statement or balance sheet since a purchase order represents an allocation of inventory and not an actual purchase (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Vendor Accounts\r Entering a new vendor \r     Editing a vendor account \r     Deleting a vendor account\r     Setting vendor payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a vendor\r Other Vendor Actions \r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r   Writing a check to a vendor\r   Issuing a vendor credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking vendor balances'),
(15, 17, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.03.04', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/03-PurchaseOrders/04-POManager.html', 'Purchase Orders.PO Manager', 'Purchase Order Manager', 'Purchase Order Manager\r \r \r \r \r Purchase Order Manager\r The purchase order manager lists all open purchase orders in the current accounting period. From this screen, the purchase order may be reviewed, inventory items may be received, and item delivery dates may be entered. The search period pull-down menu and the text search box are available to quickly locate purchase orders.\r Viewing a Purchase Order\r \r   Select Vendors-&gt;Purchase Order Manager\r   Locate the purchase order to view and press the button labeled View.\r   The Purchase Order screen will load and the form will be filled in with the information of the selected PO.\r   From here, the purchase order may be edited, deleted,  closed or reviewed. \r \r Receiving Inventory from a Purchase Order\r \r   Select Vendors-&gt;Purchase Order Manager \r   Locate the purchase order to receive against and press the button labeled ''Receive''.\r   The Purchase/Receive screen will load and the remaining items from the selected PO will be shown.\r   Receive in the quantities received for each line item.\r    Make any other changes as necessary; such as the vendors invoice number or check the Waiting for Invoice if the invoice has not been received.\r   Press the Save icon to save the inventory receipt.\r \r Changing Delivery Dates for a Purchase Order\r When a purchase order is placed, the expected delivery date is set based on the  Lead Time field specific to the inventory item. After a PO is sent to a vendor, the vendors delivery dates may not align with the items Lead Time date. the estimated delivery dates may be modified here to reflect the current estimated delivery dates for each line item on the PO. the delivery dates field is useful to identify when items are expected for filling back-orders and notifications of expected arrivals of inventory items.\r \r    Select Vendors-&gt;Purchase Order Manager \r   Locate the purchase order to adjust or view the expected delivery dates and press the button labeled ''Delivery Dates''.\r   A popup will appear listing each line item from the PO, the quantity ordered and the description. The currently expected delivery date will also be displayed.\r   If necessary, enter a new delivery date for each item on the PO. A popup calendar is provided to help locate dates. If no change is necessary, leave the date field blank to retain the current delivery date. \r   After updating all affected delivery dates, press the Save icon the save the changes and return to the Purchase Order Manager window. \r \r Related Topics\r Vendor Accounts\r Entering a new vendor \r     Editing a vendor account \r     Deleting a vendor account\r     Setting vendor payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a vendor\r Reports and Forms \r Open purchase order report'),
(16, 17, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.03.05', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/03-PurchaseOrders/05-ClosePO.html', 'Purchase Orders.CLosing', 'Closing a Vendor Purchase Order', 'Closing a Vendor Purchase Order\r \r \r \r \r Closing a Vendor Purchase Order\r Purchase  orders can  be closed for several reasons. They may be closed directly from the Edit PO screen by selecting the close button.Closed POs will not affect the inventory levels or appear in any inventory stock level calculations. POs may also be closed by SmartBooks if all the items have been received through the Purchase/Receive screen. Closing a purchase order will remove all remaining ''quantity on  order'' quantities from inventory identified in the purchase order being closed that have not been received. \r \r   From the Vendors Menu, select Purchase Orders. The Purchase Order form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the purchase orders for the current period. Select the sales order to be closed and the sales order form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired purchase order. \r   \r   Check the Close selection box.\r   Press the Save button.\r \r When a purchase order is closed, the  quantity on  order values are readjusted. This action will not affect the income statement or balance sheet since a purchase order represents an allocation of inventory and not an actual purchase (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Vendor Accounts\r Entering a new vendor \r     Editing a vendor account \r     Deleting a vendor account\r     Setting vendor payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r &nbsp;'),
(17, 33, '0', 'en_us', '07.02.03', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/03-PurchaseOrders/POHome.html', 'Vendors.Purchase Orders', 'Vendors - Purchase Orders', 'Vendors - Purchase Orders\r \r \r \r \r Vendors - Purchase Orders\r Purchase orders are used to enter inventory and services purchased from a vendor. Reports can be generated to list the inventory shortfalls and inventory purchases. Each inventory item has a minimum balance field that can be used to help identify when inventory needs to be ordered. Purchase orders do not affect your financial situation, income statement or balance sheet. they merely act as a placeholder to determine inventory stock levels needed to add or replace inventory stock levels. \r Purchase Order features:\r \r   Multiple inventory line items \r   Separate billing and shipping address \r   Drop ship ability \r    Individual general ledger accounts for each line item\r   Freight estimator to calculate shipping costs\r   Sales tax can be added to PO \r   Customizable payment terms\r \r Related Topics\r Vendor Accounts\r Entering a new vendor \r   Editing a vendor account \r   Deleting a  vendor account\r Setting vendor payment terms and credit limits \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r    Editing a purchase order\r   Deleting a purchase order\r   Closing a purchase order\r   Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a vendor\r Other Vendor Actions \r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r Writing a check to a vendor\r     Issuing a vendor credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking vendor balances\r &nbsp;'),
(18, 21, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.04.01', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/04-Quotes/01-EnterQuote.html', 'Vendor Request for Quote.Entering', 'Entering Vendor Request for Quote', 'Entering Vendor Request for Quote\r \r \r \r \r  Entering Vendor Request for Quote\r Request for Quote are used to enter purchase from a vendor. Reports can be generated to list the inventory shortfalls and inventory purchases. Each inventory item has a minimum balance field that can be used to help identify when inventory needs to be ordered. Request for Quotes do not affect your financial situation, income statement or balance sheet. they merely act as a placeholder to determine inventory stock levels needed to add or replace inventory stock levels. \r \r   From the Vendors Menu, select Request for Quote. The request for quote form will load.\r   Enter the Vendor ID and click on the open icon right of the Vendor ID window. The vendor popup window will appear. Select the vendor from the list and the information will be pre-loaded into the request for quote form.\r     \r     NOTE: The Vendor ID text box also acts as a search box to quickly find vendors.\r     \r     Vendor records consist of a main address, billing addresses and shipping addresses. Select the billing address and shipping address from the pull down menus. New addresses may be added to either the shipping or billing address if they cannot be found from either of the menus. Selecting the add/update button will update the database whereas leaving it unchecked will just retain the address for this request for quote.\r     Drop Ship - If this is a drop ship, select the Drop Ship box and the drop ship search box will appear. Customers can be searched and their shipping information will be entered into the drop down or the shipping address may be entered directly into the address fields. \r   Enter the request for quote Post Date and expected Receipt Date. Popup calendars are provided to help with the selection.\r    request for quote Number - Enter the request for quote number. If left blank, the next sequential request for quote number will be automatically generated by the system.\r    Enter the your purchase reference   number, store id and purchase representative. The default accounts payable account is loaded and can be changed. The vendor payment terms are loaded when a vendor is selected from the vendor popup. If a new vendor is entered, the default payment terms are loaded. To change the payment terms, click on the icon next to the terms text field and the terms popup will be displayed. Select the terms for this request for quote and press Save to enter the terms into the request for quote form.\r   Enter the inventory items for the request for quote. The form defaults with a single inventory line but more may be added by pressing the Add button located in the lower left area of the request for quote form. Enter the quantity requested. The item cost value assigned to the sku will be placed in the price field and the line total will be calculated. \r     \r     NOTE: The inventory SKU field also acts as a search field for the inventory popup. To quickly find an inventory item, enter part of the item sku or description and press the icon next to the SKU. The SKU, description and pricing fields will be filled in. \r     \r   Enter the inventory SKU, description and price (or retrieve from the inventory popup) for the line item. Enter more line items as necessary. \r   Enter the shipping charges (or use the shipping estimator to calculate freight charges).\r   Select  the tax authority, the tax will be automatically calculated.\r   Save or Print the request for quote. Error checking will be performed and any errors will be indicated either in a popup for errors before the form is submitted or at the top of the reloaded page (for errors during  processing). If the request for quote number field was left blank, a number will be assigned by the system. If the Print button was selected, the request for quote will be posted first followed by a popup window displaying the possible forms to print, select the form to print and press the Print button. \r \r Related Topics\r Vendor Accounts\r Entering a new vendor \r     Updating vendor information\r     Setting vendor payment terms and credit limits \r Vendor Request for Quote\r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r     Editing a request for quote\r     Deleting a request for quote  \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a vendor\r Other Vendor Actions \r   Writing a check to a vendor\r     Issuing a vendor credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking vendor balances\r Tax Authorities \r Setting up tax authorities\r    Setting up tax rates'),
(19, 21, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.04.02', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/04-Quotes/02-EditQuote.html', 'Vendor Request for Quote.Editing', 'Editing a Vendor Request for Quote', 'Editing a Vendor Request for Quote\r \r \r \r \r  Editing a Vendor Request for Quote\r Vendor purchase  quotes can only be deleted if no items have been received from the request for quote. If any items have been received, the corresponding purchase/receipt must be removed before the request for quote can be deleted. In this case, the request for quote should be closed. See Closing a request for quote. Closing a request for quote will remove all remaining ''quantity on  order'' quantities from inventory. \r \r   From the Vendors Menu, select Request for Quote. The request for quote form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the Request for Quotes for the current period. Select the sales order to be deleted and the sales order form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired request for quote. \r   \r   Press the Delete button and confirm the action on the confirmation popup.\r \r When a request for quote is deleted, the journal entry is removed from the database and the quantity on  order values are readjusted. This action will not affect the income statement or balance sheet since a request for quote represents an allocation of inventory and not an actual purchase (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Vendor Accounts\r Entering a new vendor \r     Updating vendor information\r     Setting vendor payment terms and credit limits \r Vendor Request for Quote\r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r     Editing a request for quote\r     Deleting a request for quote  \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a vendor\r Other Vendor Actions \r  Writing a check to a vendor\r     Issuing a vendor credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking vendor balances\r &nbsp;'),
(20, 21, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.04.03', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/04-Quotes/03-DeleteQuote.html', 'Vendor Request for Quote.Deleting', 'Deleting a Vendor Request for Quote', 'Deleting a Vendor Request for Quote\r \r \r \r \r  Deleting a Vendor Request for Quote\r Purchase  quotes can only be deleted if no items have been received from the request for quote. If any items have been received, the corresponding purchase/receipt must be removed before the request for quote can be deleted. In this case, the request for quote should be closed. See Closing a request for quote. Closing a request for quote will remove all remaining ''quantity on  order'' quantities from inventory. \r \r   From the Vendors Menu, select Request for Quote. The request for quote form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the Request for Quotes for the current period. Select the sales order to be deleted and the sales order form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired request for quote. \r   \r   Press the Delete button and confirm the action on the comfirmation popup.\r \r When a request for quote is deleted, the journal entry is removed from the database and the quantity on  order values are readjusted. This action will not affect the income statement or balance sheet since a request for quote represents an allocation of inventory and not an actual purchase (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Vendor Accounts\r Entering a new vendor \r     Updating vendor information\r     Setting vendor payment terms and credit limits \r Vendor Request for Quote\r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r     Editing a request for quote\r     Deleting a request for quote  \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a vendor\r Other Vendor Actions \r   Writing a check to a vendor\r     Issuing a vendor credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking vendor balances\r &nbsp;'),
(21, 33, '0', 'en_us', '07.02.04', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/04-Quotes/QuotesHome.html', 'Vendors.Request for Quotes', 'Vendors - Request for Quotes', 'Vendors - Request for Quotes\r \r \r \r \r Vendors - Request for Quotes\r Request for Quote are used to enter purchase from a vendor. Reports can be generated to list the inventory shortfalls and inventory purchases. Each inventory item has a minimum balance field that can be used to help identify when inventory needs to be ordered. Request for Quotes do not affect your financial situation, income statement or balance sheet. they merely act as a placeholder to determine inventory stock levels needed to add or replace inventory stock levels. \r Vendor Request for Quote features:\r \r   Multiple inventory line items \r   Separate billing and shipping address \r   Drop ship ability \r    Individual general ledger accounts for each line item\r   Freight estimator to calculate shipping costs\r   Sales tax can be added to PO \r   Customizable payment terms\r \r Related Topics\r Vendor Accounts\r Entering a new vendor \r     Updating vendor information\r     Setting vendor payment terms and credit limits \r Vendor Request for Quote\r Generating a request for quote (RFQ) \r   Editing a request for quote\r   Deleting a request for quote \r \r Purchase Orders\r Entering a purchase order\r     Editing a purchase order\r     Deleting a purchase order\r     Closing a purchase order\r     Checking purchase order status (Purchase Order Manager) \r Purchases/Receive Inventory\r Receiving inventory from a purchase order\r     Receiving inventory directly from a vendor\r Other Vendor Actions \r   Writing a check to a vendor\r   Issuing a vendor credit memo\r Reports and Forms \r Checking vendor balances\r &nbsp;'),
(22, 24, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.05.01', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/05-Purchases/01-ReceivePO.html', 'Vendors.Receipts from a PO', 'Receive Inventory from a Purchase Order', 'Receive Inventory from a Purchase Order\r \r \r \r \r Receive Inventory from a Purchase Order \r Vendor purchases are represented as inventory items, services and other bills received related to operating your company. Purchases affect the financial picture of your company. All purchase records are maintained in the purchase/receive journal. \r Related Topics\r Vendors\r Entering a purchase order\r   Receiving inventory directly from vendors\r   Editing a purchase/receive\r   Deleting a purchase/receive \r Inventory\r Entering inventory items \r Banking\r Paying a bill - Checks, EFTs to you suppliers and service providers.\r Writing a check to a vendor.\r Related Reports\r Checking inventory balances\r   Checking vendor account balances\r &nbsp;'),
(23, 24, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.05.02', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/05-Purchases/02-ReceiveInv.html', 'Vendors.Receipts from a vendor', 'Receive Inventory Directly from a Vendor', 'Receive Inventory Directly from a Vendor\r \r \r \r \r Receive Inventory Directly from a Vendor\r Inventory can be received directly form a vendor without a purchase order against the vendor account. \r &nbsp;\r Related Topics\r Vendors\r Entering a purchase order\r   Receiving inventory from a purchase order \r   Editing a purchase/receive\r   Deleting a purchase/receive \r Inventory\r Entering inventory items \r Banking\r Paying a bill - Checks, EFTs to you suppliers and service providers.\r Writing a check to a vendor.\r Related Reports\r Checking inventory balances\r   Checking vendor account balances\r &nbsp;'),
(24, 33, '0', 'en_us', '07.02.05', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/05-Purchases/PurchasesHome.html', 'Vendors.Purchases', 'Vendors - Purchases', 'Vendors - Purchases\r \r \r \r \r Vendors - Purchase/Receive\r Vendor purchases are represented as inventory items, services and other bills received related to operating your company. Purchases affect the financial picture of your company. All purchase records are maintained in the purchase/receive journal. \r Related Topics\r Vendors\r Entering a purchase order\r    Receiving inventory from a purchase order \r    Receiving inventory directly from vendors\r   Editing a purchase/receive\r   Deleting a purchase/receive \r   Checking vendor balances \r Inventory\r Adding inventory items\r Banking\r Paying a bill - Checks, EFTs to you suppliers and service providers.\r Writing a check to a vendor.\r Reports\r Checking inventory balances\r   Vendor history report\r \r &nbsp;'),
(25, 33, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.06', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/06-Payments/PaymentsHome.html', 'Vendors.Payments', 'Vendors - Payments', 'Vendors - Payments     Vendors - Payments Paying a vendor for products purchased.'),
(26, 33, 'd', 'en_us', '07.02.06', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/02-Vendors/06-POP/POPHome.html', 'Vendors.Point of Purchase', 'Vendors - Point of Purchase', 'Vendors - Point of Purchase     Vendors - Point of Purchase Point of purchase is the process of receiving an item and applying a payment at the time of acquisition.');
