(41, 39, 'd', 'en_us', '07.03.02.02', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/02-Contacts/02-EditContact.html', 'Customer Contacts.Editing', 'Editing a Customer Contact', 'Editing a Customer Contact\r \r \r \r \r Editing a Customer Contact \r To edit a customer record:\r \r   Select Customers-&gt;Maintain Customers page.\r   Select the Edit icon next to the customer to edit. A search box has been provided to quickly locate the customer.\r   Edit/update/change any fields for the customer.\r   Add/Delete any additional shipping or billing addresses.\r   Press the Save button to save the changes. You will be returned to the Maintain Customers page. \r \r Related Topics\r Customers\r  Adding a new customer contact \r   Deleting a customer contact \r   Setting up a customer credit limit\r Checking customer balances \r Sales Orders\r Entering  a sales order\r   Deleting a sales order\r   Closing a sales order\r &nbsp;'),
(42, 39, 'd', 'en_us', '07.03.02.03', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/02-Contacts/03-DeleteContact.html', 'Customer Contacts.Deleting', 'Deleting a Customer Contact', 'Deleting a Customer Contact\r \r \r \r \r  Deleting a Customer Contact \r NOTE: Customers cannot be deleted if they have a journal entry associated with them. \r To delete a customer record:\r \r   Select Customers-&gt;Maintain Customers page.\r   Select the Delete icon next to the customer to delete. A search box has been provided to quickly locate the customer.\r   Confirm the deletion and you will be returned to the Maintain Customers page. \r \r Related Topics\r Customers\r  Adding a new customer contact \r   Editing a customer contact \r Sales Orders\r   Deleting a sales order\r   Closing a sales order\r &nbsp;'),
(43, 39, 'd', 'en_us', '07.03.02.04', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/02-Contacts/04-PaymentTerms.html', 'Customer Accounts.Payment Terms', 'Customer Payment Terms', 'Customer Payment Terms\r \r \r \r \r Customer Payment Terms\r Customer payment terms may be set up through the configuration screen. The terms set up will be applied as the default terms for all new customer contacts. Additionally, existing contacts with out terms defined (or ''Use Standard Terms'') will track the terms defined in the configuration setup definitions. Individual customer terms may also be set up for customers whose terms are different from the standard terms. Terms may also be set up for specific sales through the Sales Order/Invoice procedure. \r Setting up Default Terms \r \r   Select Company-&gt;Customer Defaults.\r   Edit the fields as necessary. The terms type defaults to the standard X% discount in Y days, Net Z days.\r   Set the default customer credit limit to use. \r \r Setting up Customer Specific Payment Terms\r \r    Select Customers-&gt;Maintain Customers. \r   Search for the customer whose terms you want to change and press the edit icon to reach the detailed page.\r    Under the section titled Payment Terms, check the radio button for the terms type to apply to this customer.\r   Depending on the terms type selected, the Discount, Due In, Net and date fields will be active. Fill in the fields for the terms type selected.\r   Enter the credit limit for the current customer.\r   Press the Save icon to save the changes.\r \r Setting Payment Terms for a Single Purchase\r \r   Select Customers-&gt;Sales/Invoice (or Sales Order, Customer Quote).\r   On the form select the Open icon next to the terms field. A popup window will open with the current terms selected.\r   Change the terms as necessary and press Save to enter the new terms into the form.\r \r Related Topics\r Customers\r  Adding a new customer contact\r   Editing a customer contact\r Sales Orders