(133, 135, 'd', 'en_us', '03.04.02', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/04-02-BeginningBalances.html', 'Installation.Beginning Balances', 'Entering Beginning Balances', 'Entering Beginning Balances\r \r \r \r \r Entering Beginning Balances\r Unless SmartBooks is set up on a new company, there will probalby be a need to transfer beginning balances from your old accounting system.   The follwing tables define the data structures required to import inventory valuation and balances as well as Payables and Receivables balances.\r Inventory\r Before beginning balances can be set up, inventory items need to be imported (or entered) into SmartBooks. Refer to manual pages on importing/exporting data for the procedure and more information.\r NOTE: If any part of the beginning balances needs to be re-entered, the only option at this time is to purge the GL and history records through the General Ledger -&gt; Utilities -&gt; Purge Journal Entries option. Note that purging the journal entries will clean out the journals and history records. It will not affect the customer or vendor accounts. \r File format \r Type: csv (comma separated variables)\r   Delimiter: comma (,)\r   Qualifier: double-quote (&quot;)\r File extension must be .csv or .txt \r Header Lines: 1  (header fields as identifed in the table below)\r Column contents\r Each entry of the inventory beginning balances should have to following information. Required fields are marked with a *. \r \r   \r     Field Name \r     Description\r   \r   \r     *sku\r     The item sku as defined on the inventory database. Must match exactly, case sensitive. \r   \r   \r     *gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to use to offset the inventory value. This account should be an ''equity-doesn''t close'' type of account. \r   \r   \r     *inv_gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to store the inventory value. This should be and ''inventory'' type of account. \r   \r   \r     *quantity\r     The quantity of the sku to set as the beginning inventory balance.\r   \r   \r     *total_amount\r     The total value of the inventory item in the default currency. The unit cost will be calculated by dividing the total cost by the quantity.\r   \r   \r     &nbsp;\r      Serialized items - cannot be imported at this time \r     \r   \r \r Notes:\r \r    The beginning balances script will verify the sku is valid, GL accounts are valid. If any of these are found to be true, the script will terminate and no entries will be added to the databases. The script will also verify the the quantity is non-zero. If a zero quantity is found, the script will skip the entry and proceed to the next entry.\r \r Purchase Orders \r Importing purchase orders can be performed without first importing the your vendor accounts. The import routine will create the account if it cannot be found. POs with multiple line items must be consecutive to ensure that they are included in the same journal entry. \r File format \r Type: csv (comma separated variables)\r   Delimiter: comma (,)\r   Qualifier: double-quote (&quot;)\r   File extension must be .csv or .txt \r   Header Lines: 1 (header fields as identifed in the table below)\r Column contents\r Each entry of the purchase order should have to following information. Required fields are marked with a *. \r \r   \r     Field Name \r     Description\r   \r   \r     *account_id\r     The Short Name of the vendor that the purchase order should be entered against. This must match exactly to the short name of the vendor existing in the system (or it will be created).\r   \r   \r     *gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to apply the purchase order. This should be an ''accounts payable'' type of account. This account must be the same for all line items of the same PO number. \r   \r   \r     *inv_gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to use for the inventory line item. This account should be an ''inventory'' or ''expense'' type of account. \r   \r   \r     total_amount\r     The total value of the purchase order in the default currency.\r   \r   \r     freight_total\r     The total freight amount of the purchase order.\r   \r   \r     tax_total\r     The total sales tax amount of the purchase order.\r   \r   \r     *order_id\r     Purchase Order  number of this entry. Used for account tracking and payment identification.\r   \r   \r     *post_date\r     Date of the purchase order.\r   \r   \r     *bill_primary_name\r     The primary name of the accounts mailing address. Can be a company name or inidvidual name. \r   \r   \r     bill_contact\r     The contact (or attention) line for the account.\r   \r   \r     *bill_address1\r     The first mailing address line.\r   \r   \r     bill_address2\r     The second mailing address line. \r   \r   \r     *bill_city_town\r     The mailing city or town. \r   \r   \r     *bill_state_province\r     The mailing state or province. \r   \r   \r     bill_postal_code\r     The mailing postal/zip code . \r   \r   \r     *bill_country_code\r     The ISO 3 character country code. (USA, CAN, AUS, etc.) \r   \r   \r     telephone1\r     The account primary telephone number.\r   \r   \r     telephone2\r     The account altrernate telephone number.\r   \r   \r     fax\r     The account fax number.\r   \r   \r     email\r     The account e-mail address.\r   \r   \r     website\r     The acount website.\r   \r   \r     *sku\r     The line item SKU. Only one SKU per line. \r   \r   \r     *description\r     The line item description of the SKU. \r   \r   \r     *quantity\r     The quantity ordered.\r   \r   \r     *total_cost\r     The line item total price. The unit price will be calculated by (total price / quantity).\r     \r   \r \r Notes:\r \r   The billing information will be used as the bill to address for purchase orders. \r    The script will verify the account (Short Name) is valid (or a new account will be created).\r    GL accounts will be verified.\r   If the post date is not within the currently defined fiscal years (including bad format) the record will be placed in accounting period 1. \r   If any other errors are found, the script will terminate and no entries will be added to the databases. \r   If the beginning balance file is imported successfully, DO NOT REPEAT the import. The new entries will be added to the prior successful import and duplicate the payables. The import operation will not be posted unless the entire file is read in correctly and the success message is displayed.\r   The ship to address is assumed to be the company default address. \r \r Accounts Payable\r Importing payables can be performed without first importing the your vendor accounts. The import routine will create the account if it cannot be found.\r File format \r Type: csv (comma separated variables)\r   Delimiter: comma (,)\r   Qualifier: double-quote (&quot;)\r   File extension must be .csv or .txt \r   Header Lines: 1 (header fields as identifed in the table below)\r Column contents\r Each entry of the accounts payable beginning balances should have to following information. Required fields are marked with a *. \r \r   \r     Field Name \r     Description\r   \r   \r     *account_id\r     The Short Name of the vendor that the purchase order should be entered against. This must match exactly to the short name of the vendor existing in the system (or it will be created).\r   \r   \r     *gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to apply the purchase order. This account should be an ''equity-doesn''t close'' type of account. \r   \r   \r     *inv_gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to use for the inventory line item. This account should be an ''inventory'' or ''expense'' type of account. \r   \r   \r     *total_amount\r     The total value of the payable in the default currency.\r   \r   \r     freight_total\r     The total freight amount of the purchase order.\r   \r   \r     tax_total\r     The total sales tax amount of the purchase order.\r   \r   \r     order_id\r     Invoice number of this entry. Used for account tracking and payment identification. If left blank, the waiting for invoice box will be checked.\r   \r   \r     *post_date\r     Date of the invoice. Used calculate aging of payables. \r   \r   \r     *bill_primary_name\r     The primary name of the accounts mailing address. Can be a company name or inidvidual name. \r   \r   \r     bill_contact\r     The contact (or attention) line for the account.\r   \r   \r     *bill_address1\r     The first mailing address line.\r   \r   \r     bill_address2\r     The second mailing address line. \r   \r   \r     *bill_city_town\r     The mailing city or town. \r   \r   \r     *bill_state_province\r     The mailing state or province. \r   \r   \r     bill_postal_code\r     The mailing postal/zip code . \r   \r   \r     *bill_country_code\r     The ISO 3 character country code. (USA, CAN, AUS, etc.) \r   \r   \r     telephone1\r     The account primary telephone number.\r   \r   \r     telephone2\r     The account alternate telephone number.\r   \r   \r     fax\r     The account fax number.\r   \r   \r     email\r     The account e-mail address.\r   \r   \r     website\r     The acount website.\r   \r \r Notes:\r \r   The default company information will be used as the ship to address for payables and only a single line item will be entered identified as ''Beginning Balances Entry''. \r    The script will verify the account (Short Name) is valid (or a new account will be created).\r    GL accounts will be verified.\r   If the invoice is left blank or null, the Waiting For Payment flag will be set. \r   If the post date is not within the currently defined fiscal years (including bad format) the record will be placed in accounting period 1. \r   The script will verify the the invoice amount is non-zero. If a zero amount is found, the script will skip the entry and proceed to the next entry. In this case, the skipped records will be identified by row number. \r   If any other errors are found, the script will terminate and no entries will be added to the databases. \r   If the beginning balance file is imported successfully, DO NOT REPEAT the import. The new entries will be added to the prior successful import and duplicate the payables. The import operation will not be posted unless the entire file is read in correctly and the success message is displayed.\r   Vendor history accounts will not be updated by this procedure. \r   The ship to address is assumed to be the company default address. \r \r Sales Orders \r Importing sales orders can be performed without first importing the your custoemr accounts. The import routine will create the account if it cannot be found. SOs with multiple line items must be consecutive to ensure that they are included in the same journal entry. \r File format \r Type: csv (comma separated variables)\r   Delimiter: comma (,)\r   Qualifier: double-quote (&quot;)\r   File extension must be .csv or .txt \r   Header Lines: 1 (header fields as identifed in the table below)\r Column contents\r Each entry of the sales order should have to following information. Required fields are marked with a *. \r \r   \r     Field Name \r     Description\r   \r   \r     *account_id\r     The Short Name of the customer that the purchase order should be entered against. This must match exactly to the short name of the customer existing in the system (or it will be created).\r   \r   \r     *gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to apply the sales order. This should be an ''accounts receivable type of account. This account must be the same for all line items of the same sales order number. \r   \r   \r     *inv_gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to use for the inventory line item. This account should be an ''inventory'' or ''expense'' type of account. \r   \r   \r     total_amount\r     The total value of the sales order in the default currency.\r   \r   \r     freight_total\r     The total freight amount of the sales order.\r   \r   \r     tax_total\r     The total sales tax amount of the sales order.\r   \r   \r     *order_id\r     Sales Order number of this entry. Used for account tracking and payment identification.\r   \r   \r     *post_date\r     Date of the sales order.\r   \r   \r     *bill_primary_name\r     The primary name of the accounts mailing address. Can be a company name or inidvidual name. \r   \r   \r     bill_contact\r     The contact (or attention) line for the account.\r   \r   \r     *bill_address1\r     The first mailing address line.\r   \r   \r     bill_address2\r     The second mailing address line. \r   \r   \r     *bill_city_town\r     The mailing city or town. \r   \r   \r     *bill_state_province\r     The mailing state or province. \r   \r   \r     bill_postal_code\r     The mailing postal/zip code . \r   \r   \r     *bill_country_code\r     The ISO 3 character country code. (USA, CAN, AUS, etc.) \r   \r   \r     telephone1\r     The account primary telephone number.\r   \r   \r     telephone2\r     The account altrernate telephone number.\r   \r   \r     fax\r     The account fax number.\r   \r   \r     email\r     The account e-mail address.\r   \r   \r     website\r     The acount website.\r   \r   \r     ship_primary_name\r     The primary name of the accounts shipping address. Can be a company name or inidvidual name. \r   \r   \r     ship_contact\r     The contact (or attention) line for the account.\r   \r   \r     ship_address1\r     The first shipping address line.\r   \r   \r     ship_address2\r     The second shipping address line. \r   \r   \r     ship_city_town\r     The shipping city or town. \r   \r   \r     ship_state_province\r     The shipping state or province. \r   \r   \r     ship_postal_code\r     The shipping postal/zip code . \r   \r   \r     ship_country_code\r     The ISO 3 character country code. (USA, CAN, AUS, etc.) \r   \r   \r     *sku\r     The line item SKU. Only one SKU per line. \r   \r   \r     *description\r     The line item description of the SKU. \r   \r   \r     *quantity\r     The quantity ordered.\r   \r   \r     *total_cost\r     The line item total price. The unit price will be calculated by (total price / quantity).\r   \r \r Notes:\r \r   The billing information will be used as the bill to address for sales orders. \r    The script will verify the account (Short Name) is valid (or a new account will be created).\r    GL accounts will be verified.\r   If the post date is not within the currently defined fiscal years (including bad format) the record will be placed in accounting period 1. \r   If the sales order file is imported successfully, DO NOT REPEAT the import. The new entries will be added to the prior successful import and duplicate the sales orders. The import operation will not be posted unless the entire file is read in correctly and the success message is displayed.\r \r Accounts Receivable \r Before beginning balances can be set up, customers need to be imported (or entered) into SmartBooks. Refer to manual pages on importing/exporting data for the procedure and more information.\r File format \r Type: csv (comma separated variables)\r   Delimiter: comma (,)\r   Qualifier: double-quote (&quot;)\r   File extension must be .csv\r Header Lines: 1 (header fields as identifed in the table below)\r Column contents\r Each entry of the account receivables beginning balances should have to following information. Required fields are marked with a *. \r \r   \r     Field Name \r     Description\r   \r   \r     *account_id\r     The Short Name of the vendor that the invoice should be entered against. This must match exactly to the short name of the vendor existing in the system.\r   \r   \r     *gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to apply the receivable. This should be an ''accounts receivable'' type of account.\r   \r   \r     *inv_gl_acct\r     The General Ledger account ID to use to offset the payable value. This account should be an ''equity-doesn''t close'' type of account. \r   \r   \r     *total_amount\r     The total value of the receivable in the default currency.\r   \r   \r     freight_total\r     The total freight amount of the invocie.\r   \r   \r     tax_total\r     The total sales tax amount of the invoice.\r   \r   \r     order_id\r     Invoice number of this entry. Used for account tracking and payment identification. If left blank, the waiting for invoice box will be checked.\r   \r   \r     *post_date\r     Date of the invoice. Used calculate aging of payables. \r   \r   \r     *bill_primary_name\r     The primary name of the accounts mailing address. Can be a company name or inidvidual name. \r   \r   \r     bill_contact\r     The contact (or attention) line for the account.\r   \r   \r     *bill_address1\r     The first mailing address line.\r   \r   \r     bill_address2\r     The second mailing address line. \r   \r   \r     *bill_city_town\r     The mailing city or town. \r   \r   \r     *bill_state_province\r     The mailing state or province. \r   \r   \r     bill_postal_code\r     The mailing postal/zip code . \r   \r   \r     *bill_country_code\r     The ISO 3 character country code. (USA, CAN, AUS, etc.) \r   \r   \r     telephone1\r     The account primary telephone number.\r   \r   \r     telephone2\r     The account alternate telephone number.\r   \r   \r     fax\r     The account fax number.\r   \r   \r     email\r     The account e-mail address.\r   \r   \r     website\r     The acount website.\r   \r   \r     ship_primary_name\r     The primary name of the accounts shipping address. Can be a company name or inidvidual name. \r   \r   \r     ship_contact\r     The contact (or attention) line for the account.\r   \r   \r     ship_address1\r     The first shipping address line.\r   \r   \r     ship_address2\r     The second shipping address line. \r   \r   \r     ship_city_town\r     The shipping city or town. \r   \r   \r     ship_state_province\r     The shipping state or province. \r   \r   \r     ship_postal_code\r     The shipping postal/zip code . \r   \r   \r     ship_country_code\r     The ISO 3 character country code. (USA, CAN, AUS, etc.) \r   \r \r Notes:\r \r    The beginning balances script will verify the account (Short Name) is valid, GL accounts are valid, invoice number exists, and the date is invalid (including bad format). If any of these are found to not match, the script will terminate and no entries will be added to the databases. The script will also verify the the amount is non-zero. If a zero amount is found, the script will skip the entry and proceed to the next entry.\r   If the beginning balance file is imported successfully, DO NOT REPEAT the import. The new entries will be added to the prior successful import and duplicate the receivables. The import operation will not be posted unless the entire file is read in correctly and the success message is displayed.\r   Vendor history accounts will not be updated by this procedure. \r \r &nbsp;'),
(134, 135, 'd', 'en_us', '03.04.03', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/04-03-TransferingData.html', 'Installation.Transfering Data', 'Transfering data into SmartBooks', 'Transfering data into SmartBooks     Transfering data into SmartBooks Data from other sources can be entered, in bulk, to SmartBooks through the beginning balances functions and the import/export operation. Refer to the particular section for details in their respective operation. Here is the general guideline to transfering data into SmartBooks.    Complete the setup script to initilize the database. (Be sure to use you current chart of accounts)    Set-up inventory categories and fields.    Import Inventory Items, Customers, Vendors and Employees.   Import beginning Accounts Receivable, Accounts Payable, and Inventory balances.   Edit the beginning balances form to match each account with your former trial balance from the previous accounting package.   Set the current accounting period to the current period.   View the Income Statement and Balance Sheet and compare with the expected account values.'),
(135, 137, '0', 'en_us', '03.04', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/04-PostInstallation.html', 'Installation.Post-Installation', 'Post-Installation Considerations', 'Post-Installation Considerations     Post-Installation Considerations After the setup script is complete the following steps should be taken to secure your system.    Change the permissions on includes/configure.php to read-only (0x444).'),
(136, 137, 'd', 'en_us', '03.05', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/05-InstallationFAQ.html', 'Installation.FAQs', 'Common Installation Problems and Frequently Asked Questions', 'Common Installation Problems and Frequently Asked Questions     Common Installation Problems and FAQs Below are some of the common errors installing smartbooks. More current information can also be found at the SmartBooks support site, http://www.smartbooks.com/pb_phpBB/index.php. Table of Contents    Issue 1   Issue 2  Resolutions         Issue 1            Resolution 1                Issue 2            Resolution 2      &nbsp;'),
(137, 0, '0', 'en_us', '03', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/InstallationHome.html', 'Installation', 'Installation', 'Installation     Installation The section deals with installation concerns from downloading the distribution to post-installation. The Setup section contains information from the intial  login screen to intializing company information, setting users, permissions, etc. Installation topics:  Pre-installation    Pre-Requisites   Chart of Accounts    SSL Considerations   Pre-installation Checklist   The Setup Script     Running the setup script   Post-Installation    Transferring data   Setting up beginning balances   Installation FAQs    Frequently Asked Questions'),
(138, 139, 'd', 'en_us', '04.03', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch04-Setup/CharacterSets.html', 'Setup.Character Sets', 'Character Sets Setup', 'Character Sets Setup     Character Sets Setup &nbsp;'),
(139, 0, '0', 'en_us', '04', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch04-Setup/CompanySetup.html', 'Setup.Introduction', 'Company Setup', 'Company Setup     Company Setup Upon initial setup, the company information is loaded in the database. If additional companies are added, they will appear at login in a pull down menu. The user will need to select the company to use at login. Once selected, the copmpany will remain in use for the duration of the session. Additional companies can be added through the Tools-&gt;Company Manager menu.'),
(140, 139, 'd', 'en_us', '04.02', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch04-Setup/Currencies.html', 'Setup.Currencies', 'Currencies Setup', 'Currencies Setup     Currencies Setup SmartBooks supports multiple currencies. The default currency is set  during setup but additional currencies can be entered through the Setup-&gt;Currencies menu. To enter a new currency:    Select Setup-&gt;Currencies.   Enter the fields request in the popup form.    Press the Save button to save the record.   To delete a currency:    Select Setup-&gt;Currencies.   The current currencies are listed. To delete a currency, select the delete icon for the currency to delete.   Confirm the deletion of the record. NOTE: If the default currency is deleted, a new default currency should be selected.  Related Links'),
(141, 139, 'd', 'en_us', '04.01', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch04-Setup/Languages.html', 'Setup.Languages', 'Language Setup', 'Language Setup     Language Setup Languages are automatically detected at login. However, the default language can be set in the includes/configure.php file to pre-select the language during login.   The login script reviews the directories under the General module to see what language modules have been installed. Each user can select their prefered language and it will remain in effect during the duration of the session. Language modules are available throught eh Phreebooks website, www.SmartBooks.com.'),
(142, 139, 'd', 'en_us', '04.04', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch04-Setup/LocationsBranches.html', 'Setup.Multiple Locations', 'Setting up Multiple Locations', 'Setting up Multiple Locations     Setting up Multiple Locations (Branches)  SmartBooks supports multiple branches/stores. The company information is gathered during setup but branch information is entered through the Setup-&gt;Maintain Branches menu. To enter a new branch:    Select Setup-&gt;Maintain Branches.   The current branches are listed. To edit a branch, select the edit icon for the branch to edit, or, to enter a new branch press the Add button.    Enter a branch ID. Branch ID''s should not contain spaces or special characters. It is best to use an abbreviation or store number as the Branch ID.   Enter the Branch information requested by the form. Required information is identifed by a * next to the input box.   Press the Save button to save the record.   To delete a branch:    Select Setup-&gt;Maintain Branches.   The current branches are listed. To delete a branch, select the delete icon for the branch to delete.   Confirm the deletion of the record. NOTE: If the branch is used in a journal record, it cannot be deleted. Instaed, check the inactive box and the branch will no be shown on the pull down menus for the order forms.  Related Links &nbsp;'),
(143, 139, 'd', 'en_us', '04.05', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch04-Setup/MultiCompany.html', 'Setup.Multiple Companies', 'Setting up Multiple Companies', 'Setting up Multiple Companies        Setting Up Multiple Companies SmartBooks requires an unique database for each company.  NOTE: Prior to adding or copying a new company, the database must exist in the system. Phreebooks WILL NOT generate the database! Adding a new company     Go to Tools-&gt;Company Manager.   Enter the database name in the Add New Company fieldset.   Enter the company full name in the Add New Company fieldset.   If you want the demo data loaded, check the Add Demo Data box.    Click the Add New Company button.     Note: When a new comany is created, a directory under /my_files is created named the same as the database. Additional directories and  system files are created under this new directory to store uploads, logs and other information pertaining to the newly created company.   Copying a company     Go to Tools-&gt;Company Manager.   Enter the database name in the Copy Company fieldset.   Enter the company full name in the Copy Company fieldset.   Check the boxes for the information you want to transfer over to the new company.    Click the Copy Company button.     Note: When a  company is copied, a directory under /my_files is created named the same as the database. Additional directories and system files are created under this new directory to store uploads, logs and other information pertaining to the newly created company.   Deleting a company    WARNING: THIS IS A NON-RECOVERABLE EVENT! ALL DATA WILL BE LOST! BE SURE TO BACK UP YOU FILES BEFORE DELETING A COMPANY.     Select the company from the pulldown menu in the Delete Company fieldset.   Click the Delete Company button and confirm the deletion.   All company data will be erased. This includes all database tables as well as the directory (and subdirectories) under the /my_files/ directory named after the database.  &nbsp;'),
(144, 147, 'd', 'en_us', '05.01', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch05-AccountingTutorial/01-Tutorial.html', 'Tutorial.Accounting', 'Accounting Tutorial', 'Accounting Tutorial     Accounting Tutorial &nbsp;'),
(145, 147, 'd', 'en_us', '05.02', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch05-AccountingTutorial/02-Resources.html', 'Tutorial.Accounting Resources', 'Accounting Resources', 'Accounting Resources     Accounting Resources'),
(146, 147, 'd', 'en_us', '05.03', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch05-AccountingTutorial/03-PhreeBooksSpecific.html', 'Tutorial.Journal Definitions', 'SmartBooks Journal Definitions', 'SmartBooks Journal Definitions       SmartBooks Journal Definitions SmartBooks uses journals to hold transaction information. Every type of transaction includes an unique journal ID to indicate the type of transaction. The table below describes the journal ID''s and their definitions. All journal entries are stored in a two database tables, journal_main and journal_item. Table journal_main contains the general information regarding the transaction, table journal_item contains the line items associated with a transaction. For example, an invoice will contain a single journal_main record and several journal_item records. The journal_item record will have a record for the invoice total, one record for each sales tax authority, one record for shipping charges, and one record for each line item in the invoice.          SmartBooks Journal Definitions              Journal ID      Transaction Type      Description           2     General Journal     This journal records transaction directly to the general ledger. Costs are credited or debited directly to the selected general ledger accounts.            3     Purchase Quote Journal      Used to record quotes to vendors for purchases.           4     Purchase Order Journal      Used to record purchase orders placed with vendors.           6     Purchases Journal      Used to record items/action received from vendors. May or may not impact inventory. Items need net be physical, they may be bills received from vendors for services, etc.            7     Vendor Credit Memo Journal      Used to record credit memos for vendors for items returned.            8     Payroll Journal      Not used at the present time. Reserved for future payroll functionality.            9     Sales Quote Journal      Used to record quotes to customers.            10     Sales Order Journal      Used to record sales orders placed by customers.            12     Sales/Invoice Journal      Used to record sales of items, services, etc. to customers.           13     Customer Credit Memo Journal      Used to record returns by customers.           14     Inventory Assembly Journal      Used to record inventory items assembled. The inventory item must be of type Item Assembly.            16     Inventory Adjustment Journal      Used to record inventory adjustments. Adjustments may be positive (extra inventory) or negative (inventory loss due to pilferage, damage, etc.)           18     Cash Receipts Journal      This journal is used for all customer receipt type transactions. It is also used for Vendor Credit Memos.           19     Point of Sale Journal      Not used at the present time. For direct sales, enter the items through the sales/invoice journal and select the payment button to post the transaction and proceed to the payment receipt operation.            20     Cash Distribution Journal      This journal is used for all vendor payment type transactions. It is also used for Customer Payment entries.           21     Point of Purchase Journal      Not used at the present time. For direct purchases, enter the items through the purchase/receive journal and select the payment button to post the transaction and proceed to the payment operation.            22     Shipping Journal      Not used at the present time. This function is handled through the Shipping Manager.      &nbsp;'),
(147, 0, '0', 'en_us', '05', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch05-AccountingTutorial/AccoutingTutorial.html', 'Tutorial.Basic Accounting', 'Accounting Tutorial and Resources', 'Accounting Tutorial and Resources     Accounting Tutorial and Resources'),
(148, 150, 'd', 'en_us', '06.01', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch06-UsersSecurity/01-CtlPanelSecurity.html', 'Security.Control Panel', 'Control Panel Security', 'Control Panel Security     Control Panel Security The Phreebooks control panel has built in security to control user access to individual control panel modules. Permissions are based on the modules most closely related to the SmartBooks module it pertains to. For example, the sales order control panel module is tied to the permission of the Customer-&gt;Sales Orders module. If the user has no access to the Sales Order function, the control panel module will be blocked as well.  &nbsp;'),
(149, 150, 'd', 'en_us', '06.02', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch06-UsersSecurity/02-RptFrmSecurity.html', 'Security.Reports', 'Reports/Forms Security', 'Reports/Forms Security     Reports/Forms Security  Phreebooks reports and forms have three levels of security: user, employee, and department. They my be used individually or in any combination.  User security - One or more (or all by default) users may be given access to the report.  Employee - One of more (or all by default) employees may be given access to the report. Department - one or more (or all by default) departments may be given access to the report. &nbsp;'),
(150, 0, '0', 'en_us', '06', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch06-UsersSecurity/UsersMain.html', 'Users', 'Users and Security', 'Users and Security\r \r \r \r \r Users and Security\r Phreebooks support multiple users each assigned multi-level  security. During setup, the administrator user is defined and given full privileges. the administrator can then add additional users and set security appropriately. Each module has an unique securty id and can be set to the following levels:\r \r   None - No access. Users with this security will not see the module as part of the menu.\r   Read Only - The user can only open and read the information. they are not permitted to save and changes they make to the record. In this case, the Save icon will not be displayed.\r   Add - The user can create records but cannot edit them or delete them.\r   Edit - The user can add and edit a record but cannot delete the record. \r   Full - The user has full read/write access to the record.\r \r The add/edit a user:\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Users.\r   The current users are listed. To edit a user, select the Edit icon for the user to edit, or, to enter a new user press the Add button.\r    Enter/edit the fields as necessary. Enter the security levels for each module as necessary. \r     NOTE: If editting a user and  the passwords fields are left blank, the password will not be affected.\r     NOTE: \r   Users may be linked to the employee list only if the employee us set up prior to the user account. \r   Press the Save icon to save the record. NOTE: the user settings will not take effect until the user logs off and back onto the system.\r \r To delete a user:\r \r   Select Setup-&gt;Users.\r   The current users are listed. To delete a user, select the Delete icon for the user to delete.\r   Confirm you choice and the user will be removed from the database.\r \r &nbsp;'),
