(152, 0, '0', 'en_us', '08', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch08-HowTo/HowToHome.html', 'How To ...', 'How To ...', 'How To ...     How To ... Installation &nbsp; Company Setup &nbsp; Receivables &nbsp; Payables &nbsp; Inventory &nbsp; Banking &nbsp; General Ledger &nbsp; Employees &nbsp; Importing/Exporting &nbsp; Reports and Forms  &nbsp;'),
(153, 0, 'd', 'en_us', '08.03.01', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch08-HowTo/HowTo-SalesProcess.html', 'How To - Process a Sale', 'How To ... Process a Sale', 'How To ... Process a Sale\r \r \r \r \r How To ... Process a Sale \r Processing sales are a key part of the smartbooks capabilities. Prior to processing a sale there are many settings that are required. \r Pre-requisites:\r Inventory - Need something to sell\r   Customer - Someone to sell to (Note - Customers can be added on either the Sales Order or Sales/Invoice screen by checking the add/update button)\r   Sales Tax Authorities and Rates \r   Payment Methods - Cash and bank Check are loaded by default\r   Shipping Carriers - If shipping is necessary. FreeShipper is installed by default and can be used when no shipping is needed.\r Entering a Sale - The Process \r OPTIONAL - Customers -&gt; Customer Quote. The customer quote is optional and if entered, can be converted to a sales order or invoice. (conversion available in Release R1.4 and up) \r OPTIONAL - Customers -&gt; Sales Order. Enter the customer information or select from the popup menu. Required fields are indicated with a red star. Select the items to sell, price. Enter the tax (automatically calculated from pull down) and shipping carrier/method.\r Customers -&gt; Sales/Invoice. If a Sales Order was created, enter the customer name in the search box and press the open icon. The customer should be in the popup menu with a pull down showing all open sales orders. Select the sales order from the pull down or select Enter New to create a new sales/Invoice. All the information will be entered in the Sales/Invoice screen. If a Sales/Invoice will be generated new in this screen enter the information for both the billing and shipping required fields and enter the item(s) being purchased. Enter the tax and shipping carrier/methods. Leave the invoice number blank and SmartBooks will assign the next invoice number from the sequence. \r NOTE: The invoice may be printed here but will show a balance due. If a payment is to be received (Point of Sale), it is better to receive the payment and print out the receipt after the payment has been processed show the invoice shows the payment applied. \r Option 1: No payment received at this time (customer billed).\r Click on the pdf icon to print the invoice and/or packing slip. Only one form may be printed at a time. If an invoice and a packing slip are both needed, print one, open the invoice again and print the other. \r Option 2: Payment received\r Click on the payment icon (looks like a calculator) and the invoice will be posted and the Customer Receipts screen will appear. Enter the payment information and click the pdf icon to print the invoice with the payment showing.\r NOTE: To aid in reconciliation with the bank, code the Deposit Ticket ID in a way such that similar type are grouped together. For example, if you accept Visa, code all receipts using Visa as payment with a VISAyyyymmdd and they will be grouped together in the bank reconciliation operation to match with the credit card batch. Code checks DPyyyymmdd and all checks received (or part of a bank deposit) will be totaled and displayed as a single line item in the reconciliation screen. All checks that are part of a single bank deposit should have the same Deposit Ticket ID code. This technique aligns the  Deposit Slip report and the bank statements. Same with credit card batches (daily credit card receipts) and cash (to count the cash drawer at the end of the day).\r To ship the item, press Customers-&gt; Invoice Manager. Locate the invoice and press the Ship button. A popup will appear for the carrier selected. For most of the basic shipping carriers, a form to enter the tracking number, if any, and date will be displayed. This information is entered into the shipping log. For package carriers such as UPS or FedEx, the shipping screen will appear to enter the package information. Once entered, shipping labels will be generated and can be printed (on either plain paper through pdf format or thermal label printer). For these carriers, the shipping log will be filled in automatically after the labels have been generated and the tracking information is known.\r NOTE: To re-print the labels or track the package, press Tools -&gt; Shipping and select the tab of the carrier. \r &nbsp;'),
(154, 0, 'd', 'en_us', '08.04.01', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch08-HowTo/HowTo-ZenCart.html', 'ZenCart Interface', 'How To ... ZenCart Interface', 'How To ... ZenCart Interface\r \r \r \r \r How To ... Setup the ZenCart Interface\r SmartBooks has a built in interface with the ZenCart e-commerce shopping cart. The interface provide the following functionality:\r \r   Download orders from Zencart to SmartBooks\r   Upload products to ZenCart from SmartBooks \r \r Pre-requisites\r  Order Download Function - None \r Inventory Upload Function - Additional inventory fields are required to match up with the fields used in ZenCart. It is recommended that a new inventory category be added containing the fields needed for the ZenCart interface.\r \r   \r     Field Name\r     (case sensitive) \r     Field Type \r     Description\r   \r   \r     catalog\r     Checkbox\r     Used to identify products that can be uploaded to ZenCart. If the checkbox is selected, an icon will appear allowing the pdoduct to be uploaded to ZenCart. \r   \r   \r     category_id\r     TextField\r     Needs to match exactly with the category as defined in ZenCart. The ZenCart category must be the lowest level in the category tree. \r   \r   \r     manufacturer\r     TextField\r     Needs to match exactly with the manufacturer as defined in ZenCart.\r   \r \r Installing the files in ZenCart \r At the ZenCart enable website, the SmartBiz SmartBooks-ZenCart module needs to be installed. the package is available at the SmartBooks website and the ZenCart website.\r \r   Unzip the files into the Zencart folder and follow the installation instructions. \r   Install the functions desired.\r   Configure the functions per the module installation instructions. When pointing the ZenCart download functions, use url: https://yourdomain.com/SmartBooksDir/modules/soap/(function).php. i.e. order.php for downloaded orders. (HTTP:// may be used for non-SSL transactions) \r \r Installing the ZenCart Module \r \r   From the Tools -&gt; ZenCart Interface menu select the function to activate and press Install.\r   Press edit to set the parameters for the interface function (see each function detail below for parameters to set).\r   After the parameters have been set, press Update to save the changes.\r \r Setting the function parameters\r Order Download Function \r \r   After installing the function. The only parameters to set are the enable/disable checkbox and the sort order. \r \r Inventory Upload Function \r \r   Install the function if not already installed. \r   Press the Edit button to enter edit mode.\r   Click the enable checkbox.\r   Set the sort order to a non-zero value.\r    For the SmartBooks XML URL, enter https://yourdomain.com/ZencartDir/admin/soap/products.php.\r   Enter an admin username and password. This can be an existing user, or better, a new user whose activity can be monitored in the admin log file.\r   If price sheets are to be used to set the upload pricing, set the True radsio button and then select a price sheet from the pull down menu. NOTE: At least one price sheet needs to be defined to upload using price sheets. If price sheets are not used, the Retail or Full Price will be used.\r \r Using the ZenCart Functions \r Order Download Function\r \r   Orders can b downloaded by logging into your Zencart shoppping cart and selecting Customers -&gt; Orders. From the order screen an icon will be added indicating whether an order has been downloaded or not. If not, press the icon and the order will be downloaded to SmartBooks (as a sales order) and the order page will reload. The download icon for the order downloaded will not be shown indicating the order was successfully downloaded to SmartBooks. \r   If there are download errors during the process, an error message will be displayed. Fix the error and retry. \r \r Inventory Upload Function\r \r   Select Inventory -&gt; Maintain. The list of inventory items will be displayed with an upload icon appearing next to the products that have been identified as catalog items. (Catalog items are items that have the added inventory field catalog checked)\r   If there are upload errors during the process, an error message will be displayed. Fix the error and retry. \r \r Additional Information\r Adding Inventory Categories\r Adding Inventory Fields Adding Price Sheets\r &nbsp;');
