(155, 159, 'd', 'en_us', '09.01.01', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/fedex/FedExHome.html', 'Shipping Modules.FedEx', 'Shipping Modules - FedEx', 'Shipping Modules - FedEx\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - FedEx\r SmartBooks includes a shipping module to integrate with Federal Express through their APIs. Companies must have a FedEx shipper number and register with FedEx.com to request a meter number before the module will function correctly. \r Features Include:\r \r   Request for meter number.\r   Freight quotes for Ground, Home Delivery, Express, Express Freight, and Freight (Ground LTL)\r   Label generation for Express, Ground, Home Delivery, and Express Freight\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Vendor order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking integration\r   Multi-piece shipments \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install FedEx Shipping/Request a Meter Number \r \r   Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the FedEx Service row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r   Click on Install to install the FedEx module. \r   Click the FedEx row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Select True to enable the module, enter your FedEx account number and FedEx Freight number if you want to use the service. Leave the meter number field blank. Select Test Mode and your desired Printer Type. Select the services you want to offer and press Update.\r   Request a Meter Number: Click the FedEx Edit button again and press the Request a Meter Number button (which will appear if your fedex number is present but the meter number is blank). An XML request will be sent to FedEx with your company''s information (as defined in Company -&gt; My Company) and account number to register with FedEx API servers. A popup window will appear if the transaction was successful with your meter number. WRITE IT DOWN! If you accidentally un-install the module, the meter number is not saved and you will have to repeat the request. Enter the meter number in the Meter Number field and press Update. \r   FedEx requires sample labels to be mailed to them to validate the quality of the image. Refer to FedEx.com for further information.\r   After approval from FedEx with your sample labels, Edit the FedEx shipping settings and change the Test Mode to Production. You will need to request a new meter number for the production servers before an actual label can be generated. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Print a Label\r Labels can be printed manually through Shipping Manager or, for a particular invoice, through the Invoice Manager. If Invoice Manager is used, most of the information will be pre-entered into the label form. Verification of information and the package details are all that is needed. If a label is generated from Shipping Manager. the destination address must be entered and the package information.\r From Invoice Manager\r \r   Select Customers -&gt; Invoice Manager. Invoices are listed  in descending order by invoice number.\r   Locate the invoice to generate a label from and press the Ship button. NOTE: Once a package has been shipped, the button will change to Void Shipment and the invoice cannot be re-shipped. \r   A popup form will appear with most of the fields filled in. The field information is derived from the invoice itself along with default values set in the Company -&gt; Shipping Defaults settings.\r   Enter the package weight, dimensions and insurance value. If more than one package is to be shipped with this invoice (Multi-piece), press the Plus sign to add another package row. \r   After all information has been entered, press the PDF icon and the label will be retrieved from FedEx. \r   Once the label has been retrieved, the window will contain either a button to download the image (thermal printers) or a PDF image will appear in the window.\r   Print the label to the appropriate printer. NOTE: For thermal labels, the label must be printed in RAW format directly to the printer port. In this case, the label must be downloaded and saved locally, The file must then be copied (or moved) directly to the port the thermal printer is connected to. \r   Once all labels have been printed, close the label manager popup widow. \r \r From Shipping Manager\r \r   Select Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager.\r   Click on the Ship a Package button.\r   A popup form will appear with shipping default fields filled in. The field information is derived from the default values set in the Company -&gt; Shipping Defaults settings.\r   Enter the address information to ship the package. \r   Enter the package weight, dimensions and insurance value. If more than one package is to be shipped with this invoice (Multi-piece), press the Plus sign to add another package row. \r   After all information has been entered, press the PDF icon and the label will be retrieved from FedEx. \r   Once the label has been retrieved, the window will contain either a button to download the image (thermal printers) or a PDF image will appear in the window.\r   Print the label to the appropriate printer. NOTE: For thermal labels, the label must be printed in RAW format directly to the printer port. In this case, the label must be downloaded and saved locally, The file must then be copied (or moved) directly to the port the thermal printer is connected to. \r   Once all labels have been printed, close the label manager popup widow.\r \r How to Re-Print a Label\r \r       From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the package to re-print the label. Click on the printer icon on the package line. NOTE: All labels are stored in the my_files directory on the server. re-printing will not re-query FedEx but merely reload the image file from the original request. \r   Once the label has been retrieved (from your local my_files directory), the window will contain either a button to download the image (thermal printers) or a PDF image will appear in the window.\r   Print the label to the appropriate printer. NOTE: For thermal labels, the label must be printed in RAW format directly to the printer port. In this case, the label must be downloaded and saved locally, The file must then be copied (or moved) directly to the port the thermal printer is connected to. \r   Once all labels have been printed, close the label manager popup widow.\r \r How to Void a Shipment\r NOTE: Shipments can only be voided the same day the label was generated. \r \r   Packages can be deleted through either Invoice Manager or Ship Manager. \r   From Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to void the shipment. Press the Void Shipment button and a label void request will be sent to FedEx. NOTE: Once a shipment is voided, the button from that invoice in Invoice Manager will revert back to the Ship state where the shipment can be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Shipping Manager, press the delete icon next to the package you want to void. Confirm the void operation and the shipment will be deleted. NOTE: FedEx will only let an entire shipment be deleted, if the shipment contains more than one package, all packages in the shipment will be voided. \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track and click on the tracking number. \r   A new window will appear linked to the FedEx.com web site and the tracking information will be automatically entered. \r   Packages can also be tracked through the Invoice Manager. Locate the invoice to track, select the View Ship Log icon and a popup will appear with the shipment information. The tracking number will appear in the log, Click on the tracking icon next to it to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r   Shipping Manager\r   Invoice Manger'),
(156, 159, 'd', 'en_us', '09.01.02', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/flat/FlatHome.html', 'Shipping Modules.Flat Rate', 'Shipping Modules - Flat Rate', 'Shipping Modules - Flat Rate\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - Flat Rate\r \r SmartBooks includes a shipping module to calculate flat rate shipping charges. \r Features Include:\r \r   Freight quotes\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Vendor order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking information and shipping logs \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install Flat Rate Shipping Module \r \r   Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the Flat Rate row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r   Click on Install to install the Flat Rate module. \r   Click the Flat Rate row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Enter the rate information and press Save to save the changes. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Enter a Shipping Log Record\r \r    Shipping log entries are entered either through the Invoice Manager.\r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to create the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Ship button on the line the invoice appears.\r   A popup will appear with a form to enter the package information.\r   Select the Service Type, shipment/Expected receipt dates, tracking information and the shipment cost.\r   Press the Save icon to save the shipment information. NOTE: Once a shipment log entry has been generated, the button on Invoice Manager changes from Ship to Void Shipment.\r \r How to Void a Shipping Log Record\r \r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice you want to void the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Void Shipment button and the shipping log entry will be deleted. NOTE: The Invoice Manager will now allow the package to be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the shipment to void.\r   Press the Delete icon on the line of the shipment, confirm the void and the shipment record will be deleted.  \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track. \r   Since Flat Rate shipping is not tied to a particular vendor, only the tracking number will be displayed, it can now be copied to the clipboard and pasted into the carrier site to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r     Shipping Manager\r     Invoice Manger'),
(157, 159, 'd', 'en_us', '09.01.03', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/freeshipper/FreeHome.html', 'Shipping Modules.Free Shipping', 'Shipping Modules - Free Shipping', 'Shipping Modules - Free Shipping\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - Free Shipping\r \r SmartBooks includes a shipping module to calculate free shipping charges (with handling). \r Features Include:\r \r   Freight quotes\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Vendor order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking information and shipping logs \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install Freeshipper Shipping Module \r \r       Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the Freeshipper row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r       Click on Install to install the Freeshipper module. \r   Click the Freeshipper row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Enter the rate information and press Save to save the changes. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Enter a Shipping Log Record\r \r    Shipping log entries are entered either through the Invoice Manager.\r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to create the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Ship button on the line the invoice appears.\r   A popup will appear with a form to enter the package information.\r   Select the Service Type, shipment/Expected receipt dates, tracking information and the shipment cost.\r   Press the Save icon to save the shipment information. NOTE: Once a shipment log entry has been generated, the button on Invoice Manager changes from Ship to Void Shipment.\r \r How to Void a Shipping Log Record\r \r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice you want to void the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Void Shipment button and the shipping log entry will be deleted. NOTE: The Invoice Manager will now allow the package to be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the shipment to void.\r   Press the Delete icon on the line of the shipment, confirm the void and the shipment record will be deleted. \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track. \r   Since Freeshipper shipping is not tied to a particular vendor, only the tracking number will be displayed, it can now be copied to the clipboard and pasted into the carrier site to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r     Shipping Manager\r     Invoice Manger'),
(158, 159, 'd', 'en_us', '09.01.04', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/item/ItemHome.html', 'Shipping Modules.Per Item', 'Shipping Modules - Per Item', 'Shipping Modules - Per Item\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - Per Item\r \r SmartBooks includes a shipping module to calculate per item shipping charges. \r Features Include:\r \r   Freight quotes\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Vendor order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking information and shipping logs \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install Per Item Shipping Module \r \r   Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the Per Item row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r   Click on Install to install the Per Item module. \r   Click the Per Item row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Enter the rate information and press Save to save the changes. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Enter a Shipping Log Record\r \r    Shipping log entries are entered either through the Invoice Manager.\r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to create the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Ship button on the line the invoice appears.\r   A popup will appear with a form to enter the package information.\r   Select the Service Type, shipment/Expected receipt dates, tracking information and the shipment cost.\r   Press the Save icon to save the shipment information. NOTE: Once a shipment log entry has been generated, the button on Invoice Manager changes from Ship to Void Shipment.\r \r How to Void a Shipping Log Record\r \r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice you want to void the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Void Shipment button and the shipping log entry will be deleted. NOTE: The Invoice Manager will now allow the package to be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the shipment to void.\r   Press the Delete icon on the line of the shipment, confirm the void and the shipment record will be deleted. \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track. \r   Since Per Item shipping is not tied to a particular vendor, only the tracking number will be displayed, it can now be copied to the clipboard and pasted into the carrier site to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r     Shipping Manager\r     Invoice Manger'),
(159, 167, '0', 'en_us', '09.01', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/ModulesHome.html', 'Shipping Modules', 'Shipping Modules', 'Shipping Modules\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules\r \r SmartBooks has a built in Shipping Manager module to aid in the generation of rates and labels for your products. Additional modules may be added to further enhance the number of shipping options. A shipping log is kept with pertinent inforamton to monitor your packages and verify status. \r Standard Shipping Modules\r Federal Express (FedEx) - Includes rates, label generation, tracking, and logging \r United Parcel Service (UPS) - Includes rates, label generation, tracking, and logging \r United States Postal Service (USPS) - rates, logging \r Flat Rate Shipping - rates, logging \r Free Shipping - rates, logging \r Per Item Shipping - rates, logging \r Store Pickup (Will Call) - rates, logging \r Table Rate Based Shipping  - rates, logging \r Zone (State/Province) Based Shipping  - rates, logging \r Related Links\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r Invoice Manger\r Adding new Shipping Modules\r Removing Shipping Modules'),
(160, 159, 'd', 'en_us', '09.01.05', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/storepickup/WillCallHome.html', 'Shipping Modules.Will Call', 'Shipping Modules - Will Call', 'Shipping Modules - Will Call\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - Will Call\r \r SmartBooks includes a shipping module to calculate will call shipping charges. \r Features Include:\r \r   Freight quotes\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Vendor order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking information and shipping logs \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install Will Call Shipping Module \r \r   Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the Will Call row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r   Click on Install to install the Will Call module. \r   Click the Will Call row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Enter the rate information and press Save to save the changes. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Enter a Shipping Log Record\r \r    Shipping log entries are entered either through the Invoice Manager.\r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to create the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Ship button on the line the invoice appears.\r   A popup will appear with a form to enter the package information.\r   Select the Service Type, shipment/Expected receipt dates, tracking information and the shipment cost.\r   Press the Save icon to save the shipment information. NOTE: Once a shipment log entry has been generated, the button on Invoice Manager changes from Ship to Void Shipment.\r \r How to Void a Shipping Log Record\r \r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice you want to void the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Void Shipment button and the shipping log entry will be deleted. NOTE: The Invoice Manager will now allow the package to be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the shipment to void.\r   Press the Delete icon on the line of the shipment, confirm the void and the shipment record will be deleted. \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track. \r   Since Will Call shipping is not tied to a particular vendor, only the tracking number will be displayed, it can now be copied to the clipboard and pasted into the carrier site to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r     Shipping Manager\r     Invoice Manger'),
(161, 159, 'd', 'en_us', '09.01.06', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/table/TableHome.html', 'Shipping Modules.Table Rate Based Shipping', 'Shipping Modules - Table Rate Based Shipping', 'Shipping Modules - Table Rate Based Shipping\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - Table Rate Based Shipping\r \r SmartBooks includes a shipping module to calculate table based shipping charges. \r Features Include:\r \r   Freight quotes\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Vendor order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking information and shipping logs \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install Table Based Shipping Module \r \r   Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the Table Based row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r   Click on Install to install the Table Based module. \r   Click the Table Based row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Enter the rate information and press Save to save the changes. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Enter a Shipping Log Record\r \r    Shipping log entries are entered either through the Invoice Manager.\r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to create the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Ship button on the line the invoice appears.\r   A popup will appear with a form to enter the package information.\r   Select the Service Type, shipment/Expected receipt dates, tracking information and the shipment cost.\r   Press the Save icon to save the shipment information. NOTE: Once a shipment log entry has been generated, the button on Invoice Manager changes from Ship to Void Shipment.\r \r How to Void a Shipping Log Record\r \r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice you want to void the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Void Shipment button and the shipping log entry will be deleted. NOTE: The Invoice Manager will now allow the package to be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the shipment to void.\r   Press the Delete icon on the line of the shipment, confirm the void and the shipment record will be deleted. \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track. \r   Since Table Based shipping is not tied to a particular vendor, only the tracking number will be displayed, it can now be copied to the clipboard and pasted into the carrier site to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r     Shipping Manager\r     Invoice Manger'),
(162, 159, 'd', 'en_us', '09.01.07', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/ups/UPSHome.html', 'Shipping Modules.UPS', 'Shipping Modules - United Parcel Service (UPS)', 'Shipping Modules - United Parcel Service (UPS)\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - United Parcel Service (UPS)\r \r SmartBooks includes a shipping module to integrate with United Parcel Service through their APIs. Companies must have a UPS shipper number and register with UPS.com to request a meter number before the module will function correctly. \r Features Include:\r \r   Freight quotes for Air and Ground small package \r   Label generation for Air and Ground\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Vendor order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking integration\r   Multi-piece shipments \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install UPS Shipping\r NOTE: UPs requires a XML Access Key before their servers can be accessed. The access key must be acquired through UPS. Visit UPS.com to request your access key. \r \r   Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the UPS Service row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r   Click on Install to install the UPS module. \r   Click the UPS row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Select True to enable the module, enter your UPS account number.  Select Test Mode and your desired Printer Type. Select the services you want to offer and press Update.\r   Enter your UPS  XML Access Key received from UPS. \r   UPS requires sample labels to be mailed to them to validate the quality of the image. Refer to UPS.com for further information.\r   After approval from UPS with your sample labels, Edit the UPS shipping settings and change the Test Mode to Production. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Print a Label\r Labels can be printed manually through Shipping Manager or, for a particular invoice, through the Invoice Manager. If Invoice Manager is used, most of the information will be pre-entered into the label form. Verification of information and the package details are all that is needed. If a label is generated from Shipping Manager. the destination address must be entered and the package information.\r From Invoice Manager\r \r   Select Customers -&gt; Invoice Manager. Invoices are listed in descending order by invoice number.\r   Locate the invoice to generate a label from and press the Ship button. NOTE: Once a package has been shipped, the button will change to Void Shipment and the invoice cannot be re-shipped. \r   A popup form will appear with most of the fields filled in. The field information is derived from the invoice itself along with default values set in the Company -&gt; Shipping Defaults settings.\r   Enter the package weight, dimensions and insurance value. If more than one package is to be shipped with this invoice (Multi-piece), press the Plus sign to add another package row. \r   After all information has been entered, press the PDF icon and the label will be retrieved from UPS. \r   Once the label has been retrieved, the window will contain either a button to download the image (thermal printers) or a PDF image will appear in the window.\r   Print the label to the appropriate printer. NOTE: For thermal labels, the label must be printed in RAW format directly to the printer port. In this case, the label must be downloaded and saved locally, The file must then be copied (or moved) directly to the port the thermal printer is connected to. \r   Once all labels have been printed, close the label manager popup widow. \r \r From Shipping Manager\r \r   Select Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager.\r   Click on the Ship a Package button.\r   A popup form will appear with shipping default fields filled in. The field information is derived from the default values set in the Company -&gt; Shipping Defaults settings.\r   Enter the address information to ship the package. \r   Enter the package weight, dimensions and insurance value. If more than one package is to be shipped with this invoice (Multi-piece), press the Plus sign to add another package row. \r   After all information has been entered, press the PDF icon and the label will be retrieved from UPS. \r   Once the label has been retrieved, the window will contain either a button to download the image (thermal printers) or a PDF image will appear in the window.\r   Print the label to the appropriate printer. NOTE: For thermal labels, the label must be printed in RAW format directly to the printer port. In this case, the label must be downloaded and saved locally, The file must then be copied (or moved) directly to the port the thermal printer is connected to. \r   Once all labels have been printed, close the label manager popup widow.\r \r How to Re-Print a Label\r \r    From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the package to re-print the label. Click on the printer icon on the package line. NOTE: All labels are stored in the my_files directory on the server. re-printing will not re-query UPS but merely reload the image file from the original request. \r   Once the label has been retrieved (from your local my_files directory), the window will contain either a button to download the image (thermal printers) or a PDF image will appear in the window.\r   Print the label to the appropriate printer. NOTE: For thermal labels, the label must be printed in RAW format directly to the printer port. In this case, the label must be downloaded and saved locally, The file must then be copied (or moved) directly to the port the thermal printer is connected to. \r   Once all labels have been printed, close the label manager popup widow.\r \r How to Void a Shipment\r NOTE: Shipments can only be voided the same day the label was generated. \r \r   Packages can be deleted through either Invoice Manager or Ship Manager. \r   From Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to void the shipment. Press the Void Shipment button and a label void request will be sent to UPS. NOTE: Once a shipment is voided, the button from that invoice in Invoice Manager will revert back to the Ship state where the shipment can be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Shipping Manager, press the delete icon next to the package you want to void. Confirm the void operation and the shipment will be deleted. NOTE: UPS will only let an entire shipment be deleted, if the shipment contains more than one package, all packages in the shipment will be voided. \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track and click on the tracking number. \r   A new window will appear linked to the UPS.com web site and the tracking information will be automatically entered. \r   Packages can also be tracked through the Invoice Manager. Locate the invoice to track, select the View Ship Log icon and a popup will appear with the shipment information. The tracking number will appear in the log, Click on the tracking icon next to it to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r     Shipping Manager\r     Invoice Manger'),
(163, 159, 'd', 'en_us', '09.01.08', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/usps/USPSHome.html', 'Shipping Modules.USPS', 'Shipping Modules - United States Postal Service (USPS)', 'Shipping Modules - United States Postal Service (USPS)\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - United States Postal Service (USPS)\r \r SmartBooks includes a shipping module to calculate United States Postal Service (USPS) shipping charges. \r Features Include:\r \r   Freight quotes\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Vendor order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking information and shipping logs \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install USPS Shipping Module \r \r   Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the USPS row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r   Click on Install to install the USPS module. \r   Click the USPS row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Enter the rate information and press Save to save the changes. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out,