(55, 59, 'd', 'en_us', '07.03.05.01', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/05-Invoices/01-EnterInv.html', 'Invoice.Entering', 'Entering Customer Sale/Invoice', 'Entering Customer Sale/Invoice\r \r \r \r \r  Entering Customer Invoice\r Sales orders are used to enter sales to a customer. Once a invoice has been entered several events may then occur. Inventory items can be ordered (Purchase Orders), items shipped or drop-shipped, pick slips, packing slips or invoices can be generated for some or all of the items in the order as they become available in your inventory. Reports can be generated to list the inventory shortfalls inventory sales. Sales orders do not affect your financial situation, income statement or balance sheet. they merely act as a placeholder to determine inventory stock levels needed to fulfill sales. \r \r   From the Customers Menu, select Invoices. The Invoice form will load.\r   Enter the Customer ID and click on the open icon right of the Customer ID window. The customer popup window will appear. Select the customer from the list and the information will be pre-loaded into the Invoice form.\r     \r     NOTE: The Customer ID text box also acts as a search box to quickly find customers.\r     \r     Customer records consist of a main address, billing addresses and shipping addresses. Select the billing address and shipping address from the pull down menus. New addresses may be added to either the shipping or billing address if they cannot be found from either of the menus. Selecting the add/update button will update the database whereas leaving it unchecked will just retain the address for this invoice.\r     Drop Ship - If this is a drop ship, select the Drop Ship box and the drop ship search box will appear. Customers can be searched and their shipping information will be entered into the drop down or the shipping address may be entered directly into the address fields. \r   Enter the invoice Post Date and expected Ship Date. Popup calendars will help with the selection.\r    Invoice Number - Enter the invoice number. If left blank, the next invoice number will be automatically generated by the system.\r    Enter the customers purchase order number, store id and sales representative. The default accounts receivable account is loaded and can be changed. The customer payment terms are loaded when a customer is selected from the customer popup. If a new customer is entered, the default payment terms are loaded. To change the payment terms, click on the icon next to the terms text field and the terms popup will be displayed. Select the terms for this invoice and press Save to enter the terms into the invoice form.\r   Enter the inventory items for the invoice. The form defaults with a single inventory line but more may be added by pressing the Add button located in the lower left area of the invoice form. Enter the quantity requested.\r     \r     NOTE: The inventory SKU field also acts as a search field for the inventory popup. To quickly find an inventory item, enter part of the item sku or description and press the icon next to the SKU. The SKU, description and pricing fields will be filled in. \r     \r   Enter the inventory SKU, description and price (or retrieve from the inventory popup) for the line item. Enter more line items as necessary. \r   Enter the shipping charges (or use the shipping estimator to calculate freight charges).\r   Select  the tax authority, the tax will be automatically calculated.\r   Save or Print the invoice. Error checking will be performed and any errors will be indicated either in a popup for errors before the form is submitted or at the top of the reloaded page (for errors during  processing). If the Purchase Order number field was left blank, a number will be assigned by the system. If the Print button was selected, the invoice will be posted first followed by a popup window displaying the possible forms to print, select the form to print and press the Print button. \r \r Related Topics\r Customers\r Adding a new customer account \r   Updating a customer account\r   Setting up a customer credit limit\r Checking customer balances \r Tax Authorities \r Setting up tax authorities\r    Setting up tax rates\r Shipping Estimator\r Setting up the shipping estimator\r Shipping an invoice\r Sales/Invoice\r Deleting an invoice\r Editing an invoice\r Printing an invoice\r Printing an pick list/packing list\r Banking\r Receiving customer payments\r Creating a bank deposit\r Writing a check to a customer'),
(56, 59, 'd', 'en_us', '07.03.05.02', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/05-Invoices/02-EditInv.html', 'Invoice.Editing', 'Editing a Customer Invoice', 'Editing a Customer Invoice\r \r \r \r \r Editing a Customer Invoice\r Editing an invoice can be performed at any time.\r \r   From the Customers Menu, select Invoices. The Invoice form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the invoice for the current period. Select the invoice to be edited and the invoice form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired invoice. \r   \r   Enter any changes, as needed, to the invoice. If any line items form the invoice hve been shipped, that particular line item cannot be deleted or the SKU changed.\r   Press the Save button and confirm the action on the confirmation popup.\r \r When an invoice is edited, the journal entry is removed from the database and the quantity on hand values are readjusted. This action will  affect the income statement and balance sheet since an invoice represents an actual sale (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Customers\r  Adding a new customer account \r     Updating a customer account\r     Setting up a customer credit limit\r Checking customer balances \r Tax Authorities \r Setting up tax authorities\r    Setting up tax rates\r Shipping Estimator\r Setting up the shipping estimator\r   Shipping an invoice\r Invoices\r Entering an invoice\r    Deleting an invoice'),
(57, 59, 'd', 'en_us', '07.03.05.03', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/05-Invoices/03-DeleteInv.html', 'Invoice.Deleting', 'Deleting a Customer Invoice', 'Deleting a Customer Invoice\r \r \r \r \r  Deleting a Customer Invoice\r Sales orders can only be deleted if no items have been shipped from the invoice. If any items have been shipped, the corresponding invoice/sale must be removed before the invoice can be deleted. In this case, the invoice should be closed. See Closing a Invoice. Closing a invoice will remove all remaining ''quantity on invoice'' quantities from inventory. \r \r   From the Customers Menu, select Invoices. The Invoice form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the invoice for the current period. Select the invoice to be deleted and the invoice form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired purchase order. \r     \r   Press the Delete button and confirm the action on the confirmation popup.\r \r When a Invoice is deleted, the journal entry is removed from the database and the quantity on invoice values are readjusted. This action will not affect the income statement or balance sheet since a invoice represents an allocation of inventory and not an actual sale (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Invoices\r Entering an invoice\r Closing an invoice'),
(58, 59, 'd', 'en_us', '07.03.05.04', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/05-Invoices/04-InvoiceManager.html', 'Invoice.Invoice Manager', 'Invoice Manager', 'Invoice Manager\r \r \r \r \r Invoice Manager\r &nbsp;\r Related Topics\r Invoices\r Entering an invoice\r Closing an invoice'),
(59, 66, '0', 'en_us', '07.03.05', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/05-Invoices/InvoicesHome.html', 'Customers.Invoices', 'Customers - Invoices', 'Customers - Invoices\r \r \r \r \r Customers - Sales/Invoices\r Customer sales/invoices are represented as inventory items and services  offered or sold through your company to your customers. Sales affect the financial picture of your company. All sales records are maintained in the sales/invoice journal. \r Related Topics\r Customers\r Entering  a sales order\r   Invoicing inventory sold through a sales order\r   Shipping inventory sold through a sales order\r   Selling directly to customers\r Using point of sale (POS)\r   Editing an invoice\r   Deleting an invoice\r Checking customer balances \r Inventory\r Adding inventory items\r Banking\r Receiving customer payments\r   Creating a bank deposit\r   Writing a check to a customer \r Reports\r Checking inventory balances\r   Customer history report'),
(60, 66, 'd', 'en_us', '07.03.06', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/06-POS/POSHome.html', 'Customers.Point of Sale', 'Customers - Point of Sale', 'Customers - Point of Sale     Customers - Point of Sale Point of sale is processed the same as a sale/invoice except payment is received at the time of invoice. In the Sales/Invoice window press the payment button after completing the invoice to post the invoice and open the payment receipts window to process the payment and print a receipt.'),
(61, 64, 'd', 'en_us', '07.03.07.01', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/07-CreditMemo/01-EnterCrdMemo.html', 'Customer Credit Memo.Entering', 'Entering Customer Credit Memo', 'Entering Customer Credit Memo\r \r \r \r \r  Entering Customer Credit Memos\r Credit Memos are used to enter sales to a customer. Once a credit memo has been entered several events may then occur. Inventory items can be ordered (Purchase Orders), items shipped or drop-shipped, pick slips, packing slips or credit memos can be generated for some or all of the items in the order as they become available in your inventory. Reports can be generated to list the inventory shortfalls inventory sales. Credit Memos do not affect your financial situation, income statement or balance sheet. they merely act as a placeholder to determine inventory stock levels needed to fulfill sales. \r \r   From the Customers Menu, select Credit Memos. The Credit Memo form will load.\r   Enter the Customer ID and click on the open icon right of the Customer ID window. The customer popup window will appear. Select the customer from the list and the information will be pre-loaded into the Credit Memo form.\r     \r     NOTE: The Customer ID text box also acts as a search box to quickly find customers.\r     \r     Customer records consist of a main address, billing addresses and shipping addresses. Select the billing address and shipping address from the pull down menus. New addresses may be added to either the shipping or billing address if they cannot be found from either of the menus. Selecting the add/update button will update the database whereas leaving it unchecked will just retain the address for this credit memo.\r     Drop Ship - If this is a drop ship, select the Drop Ship box and the drop ship search box will appear. Customers can be searched and their shipping information will be entered into the drop down or the shipping address may be entered directly into the address fields. \r   Enter the credit memo Post Date and expected Ship Date. Popup calendars will help with the selection.\r    Credit Memo Number - Enter the credit memo number. If left blank, the next credit memo number will be automatically generated by the system.\r    Enter the customers purchase order number, store id and sales representative. The default accounts receivable account is loaded and can be changed. The customer payment terms are loaded when a customer is selected from the customer popup. If a new customer is entered, the default payment terms are loaded. To change the payment terms, click on the icon next to the terms text field and the terms popup will be displayed. Select the terms for this credit memo and press Save to enter the terms into the credit memo form.\r   Enter the inventory items for the credit memo. The form defaults with a single inventory line but more may be added by pressing the Add button located in the lower left area of the credit memo form. Enter the quantity requested.\r     \r     NOTE: The inventory SKU field also acts as a search field for the inventory popup. To quickly find an inventory item, enter part of the item sku or description and press the icon next to the SKU. The SKU, description and pricing fields will be filled in. \r     \r   Enter the inventory SKU, description and price (or retrieve from the inventory popup) for the line item. Enter more line items as necessary. \r   Enter the shipping charges (or use the shipping estimator to calculate freight charges).\r   Select  the tax authority, the tax will be automatically calculated.\r   Save or Print the credit memo. Error checking will be performed and any errors will be indicated either in a popup for errors before the form is submitted or at the top of the reloaded page (for errors during  processing). If the Purchase Order number field was left blank, a number will be assigned by the system. If the Print button was selected, the credit memo will be posted first followed by a popup window displaying the possible forms to print, select the form to print and press the Print button. \r \r Related Topics\r Customers\r Entering a new Customer\r   Updating customer information\r   Setting customer payment terms and credit limits\r Checking customer balances \r Tax Authorities \r Setting up tax authorities\r    Setting up tax rates\r Shipping Estimator\r Setting up the shipping estimator\r Receiving a credit memo\r Credit Memos\r Deleting a credit memo\r   Editing a credit memo\r Entering a credit memo\r Printing a credit memo'),
(62, 64, 'd', 'en_us', '07.03.07.02', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/07-CreditMemo/02-EditCrdMemo.html', 'Customer Credit Memo.Editing', 'Editing a Customer Credit Memo', 'Editing a Customer Credit Memo\r \r \r \r \r Editing a Customer Credit Memo\r Editing an invoice can be performed at any time.\r \r   From the Customers Menu, select Credit Memos. The Credit Memo form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the Credit Memos for the current period. Select the credit memo to be edited and the credit memo form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired credit memo. \r   \r   Enter any changes, as needed, to the credit memo. If any line items from the credit memo have been shipped, that particular line item cannot be deleted or the SKU changed.\r   Press the Save button and confirm the action on the confirmation popup.\r \r When an credit memo is edited, the journal entry is re-posted in the database and the quantity on hand values are readjusted. This action will  affect the income statement and balance sheet since a invoice represents an actual sale (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Customer Accounts\r Adding a new customer account \r    Updating a customer account\r    Setting customer payment terms and credit limits\r Checking customer balances \r Tax Authorities \r Setting up tax authorities\r    Setting up tax rates\r Shipping Estimator\r Setting up the shipping estimator\r   Shipping an invoice\r Credit Memos \r Entering a credit memo\r   Deleting a credit memo'),
(63, 64, 'd', 'en_us', '07.03.07.03', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/07-CreditMemo/03-DeleteCrdMemo.html', 'Customer Credit Memo.Deleting', 'Deleting a Customer Credit Memo', 'Deleting a Customer Credit Memo\r \r \r \r \r  Deleting a Customer Credit Memo\r Sales orders can only be deleted if no items have been shipped from the invoice. If any items have been shipped, the corresponding invoice/sale must be removed before the invoice can be deleted. In this case, the invoice should be closed. See Closing a Credit Memo. Closing a invoice will remove all remaining ''quantity on invoice'' quantities from inventory. \r \r   From the Customers Menu, select Credit Memos. The Credit Memo form will load. \r   Press the Open button and a popup will appear listing the credit memos for the current period. Select the credit memo to be deleted and the credit memo form will be filled in. \r     \r     NOTE: Use the period pull down and search box to facilitate locating the desired credit memo. \r   \r   Press the Delete button and confirm the action on the confirmation popup.\r \r When an credit memo is edited, the journal entry is removed from the database and the quantity on hand values are readjusted. This action will affect the income statement and balance sheet since a credit memo represents an actual sale (monetary transaction).\r Related Topics\r Credit Memos\r Entering a credit memo\r   Editing a credit memo\r Closing a credit memo'),
(64, 66, '0', 'en_us', '07.03.07', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/07-CreditMemo/CreditMemoHome.html', 'Customers.Credit Memos', 'Customers - Credit Memos', 'Customers - Credit Memos\r \r \r \r \r Customers - Credit Memos\r Entering a credit memo\r    Deleting a credit memo\r    Editing a credit memo\r Printing a credit memo\r &nbsp;'),
(65, 66, 'd', 'en_us', '07.03.08', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/08-Status/StatusHome.html', 'Customers.Status', 'Customers - Status', 'Customers - Status     Customers - Status Customer status.'),
(66, 118, '0', 'en_us', '07.03', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/03-Customers/CustomerHome.html', 'Customers', 'Customers Home', 'Customers Home\r \r \r \r \r Customers Home\r Customers are your purchasers of products and services provided by your company.  They are used in SmartBooks to represent people or companies that payments (receipts) are made from.  Generally, customers include anyone that you receive payments from.\r SmartBooks uses a single database table to hold vendor and customer account information. \r Customer account features include:\r \r   Fields for main account address along with unlimited branch billing  and shipping addresses.\r   Default general ledger settings for receipts (sales) \r   2 main telephone numbers; 1 fax number, email and website field\r   Customer account number\r   Assign sales representatives to individual accounts\r   Government tax re-sale number field \r   Discount and Payment terms specific to an account\r \r Related Topics\r User and Security Settings\r Setting user access security\r Setting up sales representatives\r Customer Accounts\r Entering a customer account\r   Deleting a customer account\r   Editing a customer account\r   Setting default payment terms \r   Adding branch and shipping addresses\r \r General Ledger\r Adding a general ledger sales account\r Sales\r  Enter a customer quote \r   Enter a sales order \r   Enter an invoice\r   Receiving a payment\r   Enter a customer credit memo\r   Using point of sale (POS)\r Reports and Forms\r Standard customer reports\r   Standard customer forms\r &nbsp;'),
(67, 70, 'd', 'en_us', '07.07.01.01', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/07-Employees/01-Maintenance/01-NewEmployee.html', 'Employees.Entering', 'Entering an Employee', 'Entering an Employee\r \r \r \r \r Entering an Employee\r Employee accounts include any personnel on your payroll. \r To create a new account:\r \r   Select Employees-&gt;New Employee or Select the New icon form the Employees-&gt;Maintain Employees page.\r    Enter an unique Employee ID. The Employee ID (or short name) is an unique field to identify this employee form all other customers. Maximum length is 20 characters.\r   Enter remaining Primary Contact  and Main Mailing address information. Required fields are identified by a (*).\r   Enter the employee type.\r   Enter the department the employee is part of. \r   Enter the employees Government ID number (Social Security Number). \r   Press the Save icon and the record will be saved and you will be returned to the Maintain Employees page. \r \r Related Topics\r Employees\r Changing or updating an employee information\r  Deleting an employee account\r Departments\r Adding a department\r   Editing a department\r   Deleting a department\r \r &nbsp;'),
(68, 70, 'd', 'en_us', '07.07.01.02', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/07-Employees/01-Maintenance/02-EditEmployee.html', 'Employees.Editing', 'Editing Employees', 'Editing Employees\r \r \r \r \r Editing Employees\r To edit a employee record:\r \r   Select Employees-&gt;Maintain Employees page.\r   Select the Edit icon next to the employee to edit. A search box has been provided to quickly locate the employee.\r   Edit/update/change any fields for the employee.\r   Add/Delete any additional shipping or billing addresses.\r   Press the Save button to save the changes. You will be returned to the Maintain Employees page. \r \r Related Topics\r Employees\r Adding a new employee account\r  Deleting an employee account\r Setting up a employee credit limit\r Checking employee balances \r &nbsp;\r &nbsp;'),
(69, 70, 'd', 'en_us', '07.07.01.03', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/07-Employees/01-Maintenance/03-DeleteEmployee.html', 'Employees.Deleting', 'Deleting Employees', 'Deleting Employees\r \r \r \r \r  Deleting Employees\r NOTE: Employees cannot be deleted if they have a journal entry associated with them. \r To delete a employee record:\r \r   Select Employees-&gt;Maintain Employees page.\r   Select the Delete icon next to the employee to delete. A search box has been provided to quickly locate the employee.\r   Confirm the deletion and you will be returned to the Maintain Employees page. \r \r Related Topics\r Employees\r Adding a new employee account\r  Deleting an employee account \r Checking employee balances \r &nbsp;\r &nbsp;'),
(70, 74, '0', 'en_us', '07.07.01', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/07-Employees/01-Maintenance/MaintenanceHome.html', 'Employees.Maintenance', 'Employees - Maintenance', 'Employees - Maintenance     Employees - Maintenance Employees are the people you pay wages to within your company.  Adding an employee Changing or Updating  Employee Information  Deleting an Employee'),
(71, 74, 'd', 'en_us', '07.07.02', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/07-Employees/02-Payroll/PayrollHome.html', 'Employees.Payroll', 'Employees - Payroll', 'Employees - Payroll     Employees - Payroll &nbsp;'),
(72, 74, 'd', 'en_us', '07.07.03', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/07-Employees/03-DeptTypes/DeptTypesHome.html', 'Employees.Department Types', 'Employees - Department Types', 'Employees - Department Types\r \r \r \r \r Employees - Department Types\r SmartBooks allows departments to be grouped by department types. Departments are organized in a hierarchical manner. Departments are used for reporting and to help set roles and identify your companies structure.\r Adding a Department Type \r \r   Select Employees-&gt;Department Types.\r   Press the New icon.\r   Enter the name of the department type and press Save.  \r \r Editing a Department Type \r \r   Select Employees-&gt;Department Types.\r   Press the Edit icon next to the department type to edit. A popup window will appear with the department type listed. \r   Make any necessary changes and press Save. the popup will close and the changes will be saved. \r \r Deleting a Department Type \r \r   Select Employees-&gt;Department Types.\r   Press the Delete icon next to the department type to delete. A confirmation window will appear to confirm the request. \r   Press OK to confirm the deletion and the department type will be removed from the database.\r \r Assigning an Department to a Department Type \r \r   Select Employees-&gt;Departments.\r   Press the edit icon next to the department to assign. A popup window will appear with the department information.\r   Select the department type to assign this department and press the Save icon. The department type will be assigned to the department and saved in the database. \r \r Related Topics\r Adding a Department\r   Editing a Department  \r   Deleting a Department\r &nbsp;'),
(73, 74, 'd', 'en_us', '07.07.04', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/07-Employees/04-Departments/DepartmentsHome.html', 'Employees.Departments', 'Employees - Departments', 'Employees - Departments\r \r \r \r \r Employees - Departments\r SmartBooks allows employees to be grouped by departments. Departments are organized in a hierarchical manner. Departments are used for reporting and to help set roles and identify your companies structure.\r Adding a Department \r \r   Select Employees-&gt;Departments.\r   Press the New icon. A popup will appear to enter the information. \r   Enter the Department ID. (short description of the department, department number, etc.)\r   Enter a description of the department, formal name, etc.\r     If this department is a subordinate to another department, Select the Yes button and choose the department from the drop down menu.\r   Select the type of department this department is a part of. \r   Enter the name of the department type and press Save. \r \r Editing a Department\r \r   Select Employees-&gt;Departments.\r   Press the Edit icon next to the department you wish to edit. A popup will appear with the current information fill in. \r   Make any necessary changes and  press Save to update the database.\r   \r Deleting a Department\r \r   Select Employees-&gt;Departments.\r   Press the Delete icon next to the department you wish to delete. A popup will appear to confirm the deletion. \r   Press OK to confirm the deletion and the department will be removed from the database.\r \r Assigning an Employee to a Department\r \r   Select Employees-&gt;Maintain Employees\r    Press the Edit icon next to the employee you wish to assign to a department. \r   On the employee maintain screen, select the department to assign to this employee.\r   Press the Save icon to commit your changes and update the database.\r \r Related Topics\r Adding Employees\r   Editing Employees\r   Deleting Employees  \r   Adding Department Types\r \r &nbsp;'),
(74, 118, '0', 'en_us', '07.07', 'modules/contacts/language/en_us/manual/07-Employees/EmployeesHome.html', 'Employees', 'Employees - Homepage', 'Employees - Homepage \r \r \r Employees - Homepage\r Employees are the people you pay wages to within your company. \r Adding an employee\r Changing or updating employee information\r Deleting an employee \r \r &nbsp;'),
(75, 79, 'd', 'en_us', '07.04.01.01', 'modules/smartbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/01-Maintenance/01-AddItem.html', 'Inventory.Adding', 'Inventory - Adding Inventory', 'Inventory - Adding Inventory\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Adding Inventory \r Inventory items represent the goods and services produced, bought, contracted or consumed by your company. SmartBooks offers several inventory types to help manage the various attributes of each item. Some inventory types are tracked in your companies stock (stock items, master-stock items, assemblies) while others are not. All but the documentation type affect your companies financial position.\r To better help organize your inventory items, SmartBooks has a built in category and field tool. Attributes of inventory items can be added to category groups which can then be used in reports, forms, imported, exported or transfered to interface third party applications. For example, a category named packaging may be added to the inventory items and fields for package length, width, height and weight may be added to the category. \r HINT: Before creating inventory items, setting up inventory categories and fields is recommended. If the categories and fields  are set up prior to copying inventory items, the new fields will be copied when the item is copied saving the time to re-enter the data.\r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Edit/Maintain.\r   At the bottom of the list click New.\r   Enter the SKU number for the item to create and select the inventory type form the pull down menu.\r     \r   NOTE: Duplicate SKUs are not permitted. If a SKU is entered that is already in the system, an error will be displayed and the new SKU will not be created.\r   \r    Press New to create the SKU and continue to the next screen.\r     \r   Depending on the inventory type and number of categories defined, the tabs displayed on the data entry screen will vary. The first tab and will be the System tab. If the inventory type is an assembly, the second tab will show the Bill of Materials and is used to enter the sku''s used to make up the assembly. The remaining tabs are user defined and are ordered as defined in the inventory categories set up menu. \r   \r   Enter the information for the item. Use the tabs to select each category type and enter fields for that particular category.\r   When all desired fields have been entered, press Save to save your information and return to the inventory edit/maintain window. \r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Setting inventory default accounts\r   Editing inventory items\r   Copying inventory items\r   Deleting inventory items\r   Inventory adjustments\r   Entering an inventory assembly\r   Adding an inventory field\r   Editing an inventory field \r   Deleting an inventory field\r   Adding an inventory field tab (category)\r   Editing an inventory field tab (category)\r   Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r Inventory Activities \r Using the price manager  \r   Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r   Synchronizing with other applications\r Reports\r Inventory item list\r   Inventory assembly list \r   Inventory adjustment journal\r   Inventory assembly journal'),
(76, 79, 'd', 'en_us', '07.04.01.02', 'modules/smartbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/01-Maintenance/02-EditItem.html', 'Inventory.Editing', 'Inventory - Editing Inventory', 'Inventory - Editing Inventory\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Editing Inventory \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Edit/Maintain.\r   The inventory item list screen will appear initially sorted by SKU. To locate the item you wish to edit, navigate by clicking on the sorting selection in the table head or enter a search criteria in the search box and press the Enter key on your keyboard. \r   Once you locate the item to edit, click on the edit icon  to advance to the date entry screen. \r     \r     Depending on the inventory type and number of categories defined, the tabs displayed on the data entry screen will vary. The first tab and will be the System tab. If the inventory type is an assembly, the second tab will show the Bill of Materials and is used to enter the skus used to make up the assembly. The remaining tabs are user defined and are ordered as defined in the inventory categories set up menu. \r   \r   Enter the information for the item. Use the tabs to select each category type and enter fields for that particular category.\r     \r     Note: Some fields may not be editable once certain journal entries have been made. For example, the cost method will be locked out once that item has been used in for a journal activity. Other fields are system maintained and cannot be changed. These fields are either read only or disabled and cannot be changed on the form. \r   \r   When all desired fields have been entered, press Update to save your information and return to the inventory edit/maintain window.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Setting inventory default accounts\r   Adding inventory items\r   Copying inventory items\r   Deleting inventory items \r   Inventory adjustments\r   Entering an inventory assembly\r   Adding an inventory field\r   Editing an inventory field \r   Deleting an inventory field\r   Adding an inventory field tab (category)\r   Editing an inventory field tab (category)\r   Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r Inventory Activities \r Using the price manager\r   Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r   Synchronizing with other applications\r Reports\r Inventory item list\r   Inventory assembly list \r   Inventory adjustment journal\r   Inventory assembly journal'),
(77, 79, 'd', 'en_us', '07.04.01.03', 'modules/smartbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/01-Maintenance/03-CopyItem.html', 'Inventory.Copying', 'Inventory - Copying Inventory', 'Inventory - Copying Inventory\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Copying Inventory \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Edit/Maintain.\r   The inventory item list screen will appear initially sorted by SKU. To locate the item you wish to copy, navigate by clicking on the sorting selection in the table head or enter a search criteria in the search box and press the Enter key on your keyboard. \r   Once you locate the item to copy, click on the copy icon  and a popup window will appear requesting a SKU for the new item.\r   Enter the new SKU into the field and press OK to advance to the data entry screen. Most of the fields from the source item will be copied to the new item and will be shown on the form. Certain system items, such as quantity on hand, quantity on order, quantity on sales order will not be copied over and these fields will be initially set to zero. \r     \r     Depending on the inventory type and number of categories defined, the tabs displayed on the data entry screen will vary. The first tab and will be the System tab. If the inventory type is an assembly, the second tab will show the Bill of Materials and is used to enter the sku''s used to make up the assembly. The remaining tabs are user defined and are ordered as defined in the inventory categories set up menu. \r   \r   Enter/change the information for the newly copied item. Use the tabs to select each category type and enter fields for that particular category.\r     \r     Note: Some fields may not be editable once certain journal entries have been made. For example, the cost method will be locked out once that item has been used in for a journal activity. Other fields are system maintained and cannot be changed. These fields are either read only or disabled and cannot be changed on the form. \r   \r   When all desired fields have been entered, press Update to save your information and return to the inventory edit/maintain window.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Setting inventory default accounts\r   Adding inventory items\r   Editing inventory items \r   Deleting inventory items \r   Inventory adjustments\r   Entering an inventory assembly\r   Adding an inventory field\r   Editing an inventory field \r   Deleting an inventory field\r   Adding an inventory field tab (category)\r   Editing an inventory field tab (category)\r   Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r Inventory Activities \r Using the price manager\r   Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r   Synchronizing with other applications\r Reports\r Inventory item list\r   Inventory assembly list \r   Inventory adjustment journal\r   Inventory assembly journal'),
(78, 79, 'd', 'en_us', '07.04.01.04', 'modules/smartbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/01-Maintenance/04-DeleteItem.html', 'Inventory.Deleting', 'Inventory - Deleting Inventory', 'Inventory - Deleting Inventory\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Deleting Inventory \r Note: An inventory item cannot be deleted if there are journal entries posted with the item. If the user tries to delete an item that has been posted to the journal, an error will be displayed and the item will not be deleted. Once all journal entries related to this item have been removed, the item can be deleted. If this is not possible, consider marking the SKU as inactive.\r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Edit/Maintain.\r   The inventory item list screen will appear initially sorted by SKU. To locate the item you wish to edit, navigate by clicking on the sorting selection in the table head or enter a search criteria in the search box and press the Enter key on your keyboard. \r   Once you locate the item to edit, click on the delete icon   and a popup window will appear confirming the delete operation.\r   Click OK to confirm the delete operation and the item will be removed from the database.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Setting inventory default accounts\r   Adding inventory items\r   Editing inventory items \r   Copying inventory items\r   Inventory adjustments\r   Entering an inventory assembly\r   Adding an inventory field\r   Editing an inventory field \r   Deleting an inventory field\r   Adding an inventory field tab (category)\r   Editing an inventory field tab (category)\r   Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r Inventory Activities \r Using the price manager\r   Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r   Synchronizing with other applications\r Reports\r Inventory item list\r   Inventory assembly list \r   Inventory adjustment journal\r   Inventory assembly journal'),
(79, 92, '0', 'en_us', '07.04.01', 'modules/smartbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/01-Maintenance/MaintenanceHome.html', 'Inventory.Maintenance', 'Inventory - Maintenance', 'Inventory - Maintenance\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Maintenance\r Inventory items represent the goods and services produced, bought, contracted or consumed by your company. SmartBooks offers several inventory types to help manage the various attributes of each item. Some inventory types are tracked in your companies stock (stock items, master-stock items, assemblies) while others are not. All but the documentation type affect your companies financial position.\r To better help organize your inventory items, SmartBooks has a built in category and field tool. Attributes of inventory items can be added to category groups which can then be used in reports, forms, imported, exported or transfered to interface third party applications. For example, a category named packaging may be added to the inventory items and fields for package length, width, height and weight may be added to the category. \r HINT: Before creating inventory items, setting up inventory categories and fields is recommended. If the categories and fields  are set up prior to copying inventory items, the new fields will be copied when the item is copied saving the time to re-enter the data.\r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Setting inventory default accounts\r   Adding inventory items\r   Editing inventory items\r   Copying inventory items\r   Deleting inventory items\r   Inventory adjustments\r   Entering an inventory assembly\r   Adding an inventory field\r   Editing an inventory field \r   Deleting an inventory field\r   Adding an inventory field tab (category)\r   Editing an inventory field tab (category)\r   Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r Inventory Activities \r Using the price manager  \r  Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r   Synchronizing with other applications'),
(80, 82, 'd', 'en_us', '07.04.02.01', 'modules/smartbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/02-Adjustments/01-AdjustmentEdit.html', 'Inventory.Adjustments - Edit', 'Inventory - Adjustments (Edit)', 'Inventory - Adjustments (Edit)\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Adjustments (Edit) \r Edit inventory adjustment procedure \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Adjustments.\r   Press the Open button to display the inventory adjustment popup window. \r   Select the adjustment to edit by clicking anywhere on the row of the adjustment.\r   Change any fields as necessary. \r   Press Save to post the transaction to the journal. Note: Editing a journal entry first un-posts the original transaction and re-posts with the new data. Cost of good sold will be recalculated based on the post date of the edited adjustment. \r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r     Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Deleting inventory items \r     Inventory adjustment\r     Deleting an inventory adjustment\r     \r   Inventory assemblies\r   Adding an inventory field\r   Editing an inventory field\r   Deleting an inventory field\r   Adding an inventory category \r   Editing an inventory category \r Deleting an inventory category\r &nbsp;'),
(81, 82, 'd', 'en_us', '07.04.02.02', 'modules/smartbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/02-Adjustments/02-AdjustmentDelete.html', 'Inventory.Adjustments - Delete', 'Inventory - Adjustments (Delete)', 'Inventory - Adjustments (Delete)\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Adjustments (Delete) \r Delete inventory adjustment procedure \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Adjustments.\r   Press the Open button to display the inventory adjustment popup window. \r   Select the adjustment to delete by clicking anywhere on the row of the adjustment.\r   Press the Delete button and confirm you selection to un-post the transaction from the journal.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Setting inventory default accounts\r     Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Deleting inventory items \r     Inventory adjustments\r     Edit an inventory adjustment\r      \r   Inventory assemblies\r   Adding an inventory field\r   Editing an inventory field\r   Deleting an inventory field\r   Adding an inventory category \r   Editing an inventory category \r Deleting an inventory category\r &nbsp;'),
(82, 92, '0', 'en_us', '07.04.02', 'modules/smartbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/02-Adjustments/AdjustmentsHome.html', 'Inventory.Adjustments', 'Inventory - Adjustments', 'Inventory - Adjustments\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Adjustments\r Inventory adjustments are necessary when your physical inventory stock  counts do not match the calculated count within SmartBooks. An inventory adjustment will be necessary to synchronize SmartBooks with physical inventory. The two possible adjustments are increase in inventory (less physical inventory on hand than expected) and reduce inventory (more physical inventory on hand than expected). \r Inventory adjustment procedure \r  Inventory shortages can occur form many ways. Pilferage, damage, loss are a few. The stock counts within SmartBooks will need to be adjusted to match the actual stock on hand. \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Adjustments.\r   Enter the SKU or a search criteria and press the open icon  . \r   Select the SKU to adjust from the popup menu to fill in the item attributes (or if there is only one match, the popup window will close and fill in the necessary information).\r   Enter a reference for this transaction (i.e. ADJ2007-05-12).\r   Enter the post date of the adjustment or use the popup calendar to select a post date. Today''s date is loaded by default. \r   Select the GL account popup icon  and select the account to apply the adjustment. \r   Enter the total cost of the adjustment. This value only applies to increases in inventory. For inventory decreases, the cost field is ignored and the cost is calculated by SmartBooks using the items cost method and historical purchase prices.\r   Enter the adjustment quantity.\r   Enter a reason for adjustment. (i.e. damaged, expired, etc.) \r   Press Save to post the transaction to the journal. \r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r Setting inventory default accounts\r     Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Deleting inventory items\r     Edit an inventory adjustment\r     Deleting an inventory adjustment\r     Inventory assemblies\r     Adding an inventory field\r     Editing an inventory field \r     Deleting an inventory field\r     Adding an inventory field tab (category)\r     Editing an inventory field tab (category)\r     Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r &nbsp;'),
(83, 85, 'd', 'en_us', '07.04.03.01', 'modules/smartbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/03-Assemblies/01-AssembliesEdit.html', 'Inventory.Assemblies - Edit', 'Inventory - Assemblies (Edit)', 'Inventory - Assemblies (Edit)\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Assemblies (Edit) \r Edit inventory adjustment procedure \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Assemblies.\r   Press the Open button to display the inventory assemblies popup window. \r   Select the assembly to edit by clicking anywhere on the row of the assembly.\r   Change any fields as necessary. \r   Press Save to post the transaction to the journal. Note: Editing a journal entry first un-posts the original transaction and re-posts with the new data. Cost of good sold will be recalculated based on the post date of the edited adjustment.\r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r  Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Deleting inventory items\r     Inventory adjustments\r     Inventory assemblies - Delete\r     Inventory assemblies   \r     Adding an inventory field\r     Editing an inventory field\r     Deleting an inventory field\r     Adding Inventory field tabs (categories)\r     Editing an inventory field tab (category) \r     Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r &nbsp;'),
(84, 85, 'd', 'en_us', '07.04.03.02', 'modules/smartbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/03-Assemblies/02-AssembliesDelete.html', 'Inventory.Assemblies - Delete', 'Inventory - Assemblies (Delete)', 'Inventory - Assemblies (Delete)\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Assemblies (Delete)\r Delete inventory assembly procedure \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Assemblies.\r   Press the Open button to display the inventory assembly popup window. \r   Select the assembly to delete by clicking anywhere on the row of the adjustment.\r   Press the Delete button and  confirm you selection to un-post the transaction from the journal.\r \r &nbsp;\r Related Topics\r Inventory\r  Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Deleting inventory items \r     Inventory adjustments\r     Inventory assemblies   \r     Inventory assemblies - Edit\r     Inventory assemblies - Delete     \r     Adding an inventory field\r     Editing an inventory field\r     Deleting an inventory field\r     Adding Inventory field tabs (categories)\r     Editing an inventory field tab (category) \r     Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r &nbsp;'),
(85, 92, '0', 'en_us', '07.04.03', 'modules/smartbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/03-Assemblies/AssembliesHome.html', 'Inventory.Assemblies', 'Inventory - Assemblies', 'Inventory - Assemblies\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Assemblies\r Inventory assemblies are inventory items that are comprised of one or more other inventory items. When an inventory item is created, the inventory type is selected at the time the SKU is entered to identify the characteristics of the item. When the assembly type is selected the item is assumed to be made up with other items from the inventory database. In order to sell an assembly type item, it must be assembled in SmartBooks to show stock on hand. Note that an assembled item may also be purchased directly in which case inventory will show stock but no assemblies were necessary. \r Inventory assembly procedure \r \r   From the main menu, select Inventory-&gt;Assemblies.\r   Enter the SKU or a search criteria and press the open icon . Note: Only inventory items of type ''assembly'' will be displayed in the popup.\r   Select the SKU to assemble from the popup menu to fill in the item attributes (or if there is only one match, the popup window will close and fill in the necessary information). A list will be displayed of the required items and quantities needed to assemble the item and shortages will be displayed in red.\r   Enter a reference for this transaction (i.e. ADJ2007-05-12).\r   Enter the post date of the adjustment or use the popup calendar to select a post date. Today''s date is loaded by default. \r   Enter the total number of units to assemble. After the number of units to assemble is entered, SmartBooks calculates the number of required  items to build the requested amount and will warn if there are not enough pieces to build.\r   Press Save to post the transaction to the journal. \r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r  Inventory assemblies - Edit\r     Inventory assemblies - Delete\r     Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Deleting inventory items\r     Inventory adjustments - Adding \r     Adding an inventory field\r     Editing an inventory field\r     Deleting an inventory field\r     Adding Inventory field tabs (categories)\r     Editing an inventory field tab (category) \r     Deleting an inventory field tab (category)\r &nbsp;'),
(86, 88, 'd', 'en_us', '07.04.04.01', 'modules/smartbooks/language/en_us/manual/04-Inventory/04-Tabs/01-TabsEdit.html', 'Inventory.Tabs - Edit', 'Inventory - Tabs (Category) (Edit)', 'Inventory - Tabs (Category) (Edit)\r \r \r \r \r Inventory - Tabs (Category) (Edit)\r Editing an Inventory Tab (Category)\r \r   From the main menu select Inventory-&gt;Setup Inventory Field Tabs.\r   Click anywhere on the row to highlight.\r   Press the Edit button. \r   Edit the inventory tab fields. \r   Press Update to save your changes. \r \r Related Topics\r Inventory\r  Adding inventory items\r     Editing inventory items\r     Copying inventory items\r     Inventory adjustments\r     Inventory tabs (categories)\r     Deleting an inventory tab (category)\r     Inventory fields\r     Editing an inventory field\r     Deleting an inventory field\r Import/Export\r Importing Inventory\r   Exporting inventory\r &nbsp;');
