(121, 123, 'd', 'en_us', '01.05', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch01-Introduction/roadmap.html', 'Development Roadmap', 'SmartBooks Development Roadmap', 'SmartBooks Development Roadmap     SmartBooks Development Roadmap Here is a list of the future development and feature enhancement activities to complete. This list is not in any kind of prioritized order.    Additional language translations   Add Payroll Module   Add Quality Module            Document control system       RMA system           Add more payment methods   Add more shipping methods   Build more reports/forms    Complete the bulk payment script    Add manufacturing module            Work orders       Manufacturing procedures            Add more control panel modules'),
(122, 123, 'd', 'en_us', '01.03', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch01-Introduction/support.html', 'Support', 'SmartBooks Support', 'SmartBooks Support     SmartBooks Support Phreebooks has three levels of support. The SmartBooks BBS with support from the community.  Developers support through the sourceforge mailing lists.  Paid support through the SmartBiz website.'),
(123, 0, '0', 'en_us', '01', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch01-Introduction/welcome.html', 'Introduction', 'Introduction', 'Introduction     Introduction This manual is organized as follows:  Chapter 1 - Introduction Chapter 2 - General Information Chapter 3 - Installation Chapter 4 - Company Setup Chapter 5 - Accounting Tutorial and Resources Chapter 6 - Users and Security Chapter 7 - Users Manual  Chapter 8 - How To''s Chapter 9 - Shipping Modules Chapter 10 - Importing and Exporting Chapter 11 - Reports and Forms Chapter 12 - XML Interfaces Chapter 13 - Error Messages Chapter 14 - Payment Modules  Chapter 15 - Programmer''s Reference Chapter 16 - Test Specification Chapter 17 -  Chapter 18 -  Chapter 19 -  Chapter 20 - Glossary'),
(124, 125, 'd', 'en_us', '02.02', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch02-GeneralInformation/Features.html', 'SmartBooks.Features', 'SmartBooks Features', 'SmartBooks Features     SmartBooks Features SmartBooks was created as a full featured ERP/accounting system designed to run in an internet environment. Based on the administrator interface of the well established ZenCart shopping cart application. SmartBooks features include: Full Featured Installation Script     Derived from the fabulous installation script used in Zencart. Phreebooks will guide you through the installation including the chart of accounts, fiscal years and default cost account settings.   Customer Features     Individual customer credit terms    Unlimited shipping and billing addresses   Individual sales accounts    Receive payments through large number of payment modules, checks, and cash    Sales Orders, Invoices and Point of Sale capability   Full featured order status window allow for easy organization and review of orders at all status levels   Vendor Features     Individual vendor payment terms   Unilimed vendor ship from addresses and remit to addresses    Individually assignable expense accounts   Inventory Features     Handles different types of inventory items: Stock, Assemblies, Master Stock, Non-Stock, Service, Labor, and Description Only    Individual inventory cost methods: FIFO, LIFO, and Average    Multi-tier pricing, up to 5 price levels   Inventory Stock level management   Individually assigned cost accounts for sales, inventory, and cost of sales    Serial number tracking capability    Customizable inventory group/field manager. Add as many inventory attributes as needed, in as many groupings as needed to help organize and fully define you products   Banking Features     Receive payments from customers   Pay vendors, write checks directly from SmartBooks   Payment manager allow payments of multiple vendors at a time    Reconcile receipts/payments with bank statement   Handle Payroll with employees (future upgrade)   Human Resources Features    Maintain employee information   Linked to the payroll feature   Import/Export Features    Extensive/programmable export feature allow for individual field selection, order   Allows fields to be processed prior to export (e.g. format a currency, round a number, etc.)    Filters allow for selective exporting of just the fields desired    User selected field delimiters and text qualifiers to create common csv and tsv (tabbed) formats   Export of customer, vendor, inventory, banking, employee and general ledger data  External Interfaces    Modularized interfaces available to third party applications   Included interface to ZenCart shopping cart system    Download online orders from shopping cart systems with a push of a button   Upload product information from SmartBooks to your shopping cart system to allow for a single database solution   Multi-Company Features     Capable of handling multiple companies with individual databases.   New companies can be created through the setup script or copied from an existing company  Report/Form Features    Includes many standard reports and forms to get up and running out of the box   Robust report builder tool allows creation of custom reports and forms   Ability to create documents in A3, A4 and Letter size paper, portrait and landscape orientation   Payment Modules     Payment modules to allow for multiple payment methods   Easily expanded with additional payment modules   Shipping/Freight Features    Modular shipping tool allows for direct interfacing to many popular freight cariers   Included modules: free shipping, flat rate, UPS, FedEx, and more.    Shipping manager tool allows for multi-piece shipments that exceed the individual package weight allowed by carriers    Shipping tool links directly to the order screens. Ship from and ship to addresses automatically fill the shipping manager window and drops freight selection back into order, reducing errors   Security    Every menu choice has programmed security access (none, read-only, enter, edit and full) on an individual user level   Runs under a SSL or non-SSL environment    Separate user account for each company (in a multi-company environment)   Other Features    Uses pop-up windows to quickly navigate and locate the information you need   Based on the full featured ZenCart shopping cart system administrator menu   Style sheet templates are compatible with the ZenCart template definitions to create a common ''look and feel'' across the two applications    Backup feature to protect valuable company data    Multi-language feature allows individual users to operate in the language of their choice    Platform independent   Web based to allow access from any browser, anywhere   &nbsp;'),
(125, 0, '0', 'en_us', '02', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch02-GeneralInformation/GeneralInformation.html', 'SmartBooks.General Information', 'General Information', 'General Information     General Information This section covers the general information and overview of the SmartBooks ERP system.  SmartBooks Features SmartBooks Project Goals'),
(126, 125, 'd', 'en_us', '02.01', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch02-GeneralInformation/ProjectGoals.html', 'SmartBooks.Goals', 'Project Goals and Objectives', 'Project Goals and Objectives     Project Goals and Objectives The goals of SmartBooks is to develop a multi-language, accounting/ERP application freely available to everyone. SmartBooks is targeted toward the SOHO and small business community.'),
(127, 137, 'd', 'en_us', '03.01', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/01-PreRequisites.html', 'Installation.Pre-requisites', 'Pre-requisites', 'Pre-requisites     Pre-requisites Prior to running the setup script. the following items need to be verified: System Requirements  During the setup script, SmartBooks will inspect your system and let you know of any missing or downlevel pre-requisites. The setup script will not continue until these pre-requisites are met.    Mysql Version: 4.0 or higher    PHP Version: 5.0 and higher   Customization Requirements     To load your own chart of accounts (versus one of the example charts), a file needs to be generated and put into the /modules/install/charts directory. Refer to the chart of accounts help file for format information.'),
(128, 130, 'd', 'en_us', '03.02.01', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/02-01-ChartOfAccounts.html', 'Installation.Chart of Accounts', 'Example Chart of Accounts', 'Example Chart of Accounts\r \r \r \r \r  Chart of Accounts\r SmartBooks contains several example chart of accounts that can be entered during setup. There is also a provision to import your own chart of accounts during the set-up process. Your custom chart of accounts file should be placed into the directory /modules/install/charts before the setup script is executed. The file requirements are as follows:\r File Type: Text (.php extension)\r   Format: php syntax as follows:\r Comments -  preceeded by a //\r   Variable $chart_description - defines the title of the chart of accounts\r   Autoincrement Array Variable $chart_array - contains three elements (1) Account Number (alphanumeric), (2) Description, (3) Account_type code.\r The Account types are:\r 0 - Cash\r   2 - Accounts Receivable\r   4 - Inventory\r   6 - Other Current Assets\r   8 - Fixed Assets\r   10 - Accumulated Depreciation\r   12 - Other Assets\r   20 - Accounts Payable\r   22 - Other Current Liabilities\r   24 - Long Term Liabilities\r   30 - Income\r   32 - Cost of Sales\r   34 - Expenses\r   40 - Equity - Doesn\\''t Close\r   42 - Equity - Gets Closed\r   44 - Equity - Retained Earnings\r \r The example below is a snippet from the USA General Retail chart of accounts: \r &lt;?php\r   // Chart of Accounts for USA simple General company\r   $chart_description = &quot;US - General store simple Chart of Accounts&quot;;\r $chart_array = array();\r $chart_array[] = array(''1060'',''Checking Account'',''0'');\r   $chart_array[] = array(''1065'',''Petty Cash'',''0'');\r   $chart_array[] = array(''1200'',''Accounts Receivables'',''2'');\r   $chart_array[] = array(''1205'',''Allowance for doubtful accounts'',''2'');\r   \r .\r .\r .\r $chart_array[] = array(''5800'',''Licenses'',''34'');\r $chart_array[] = array(''5810'',''Foreign Exchange Loss'',''34'');\r ?&gt;'),
(129, 130, 'd', 'en_us', '03.02.02', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/02-02-SSLFactors.html', 'Installation.SSL Considerations', 'To SSL or not to SSL', 'To SSL or not to SSL     To SSL or not to SSL SmartBooks can run in either an secure SSL environment or non-SSL environment. Although it is not necessary to determine in which mode to operate prior to running the setup script, it is prefered. Changing the operating mode is possible by editting the includes/configure.php file.'),
(130, 137, '0', 'en_us', '03.02', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/02-PreInstallInfo.html', 'Installation.Data Pre-requisites', 'Pre-installation Required Information', 'Pre-installation Required Information     Pre-installation Required Information User the following checklist to help in verifying you have all the information necesary prior to running the setup script.         Complete     Description           &nbsp;     Download and unpack the necessary files            &nbsp;     Upload the files to your server in the desired directory           &nbsp;     Create the database table (note the database name, username, and user password)                &nbsp;     &nbsp;           &nbsp;     &nbsp;           &nbsp;     &nbsp;           &nbsp;     &nbsp;           &nbsp;     &nbsp;           &nbsp;     &nbsp;     &nbsp;'),
(131, 137, 'd', 'en_us', '03.03', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/03-SetupScript.html', 'Installation.Setup Script', 'Running the Setup Script', 'Running the Setup Script     Running the Setup Script Prior to setup you will want to ensure that the directory you are installing to is accessible from a web browser. You will also want to ensure that you have access to a database and have the database name, user name and password.   Unzip file into the desired directory on your server.  In a web browser, go to the location you unzipped the files to. You should receive a message stating that the configure.php was not found and a link to install the program. When you click the link you will be taken to the welcome page.  Welcome You can read read through the information on the welcome page and then click continue.  License Read and accept the user license and click continue.  Prerequisites The installer will now check for the required files and directories. If there are any unmet dependencies that prevent continuing installation these will be shown in a warning box at the top of the page. You can click the ''more info'' link next to unmet dependencies for information on how to fix the problem.  It is common for the MySQL database to be in red since the program may not yet have access to the database. This WIL NOT prevent installation.  You will also want to look at the bottom of the prerequisites page to ensure you have the correct file permissions set.  Once all of the required dependencies are met you can click install at the bottom of the page.  System Setup You will now be  asked the enter the directory or http(s) paths you want to use for various services.  You can change these if you like but the defaults should work for most installations. You will also be asked if you want to enable SSL.  Unless you know you have SSL working and want to use it you should leave this set to ''NO''.  Select ''Save Settings'' once you have finished filling out all the boxes.  Database Setup Database Type - Select the type of database you are using from the drop down menu.  Database Table - Prefix - In most cases this will be left blank.  You can enter a prefix if you are using a single database for multiple applications.  Database Host - Default is localhost but you may enter another host name or IP address if database is not hosted locally.  Database Username - Username you entered when setting up database.  Database Password - Password you entered when setting up database.  Company Database Name - Enter the name of the database you setup.  Contact the hosting provider if you are unsure.  Admin Setup Enter your Administrator name, password and email.  You can also choose whether you would like to check for updates when logging in.  Company Setup Enter your company''s information and click save.  Chart of Accounts Choose a chart of accounts most appropriate for your company.  Details of each chart can be viewed by selecting an account type and clicking ''view chart details'' link. Save settings once you have made your selection.  Fiscal Year Setup Choose the date and year you want your fiscal year to begin and save.  Account Defaults SmartBooks will attempt to determine the correct account numbers for the given items.  This can be changed later but now is a good time to ensure that all of the account numbers are correct for the given items.  Finished Your setup of SmartBooks is now complete.  This page will provide some information on further steps to help you configure SmartBooks for your company''s needs.  Make sure you set permissions on your configure.php, located in the /includes folder, back to read only.  Remove or rename your modules/install folder so that the system cannot be re-installed which would wipe out your existing database.'),
(132, 135, 'd', 'en_us', '03.04.01', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch03-Installation/04-01-configPHP.html', 'Installation.Modifying configure.php', 'Modifying configure.php', 'Modifying configure.php     Modifying configure.php The file /includes/configure.php contains critical setup information necessary to run SmartBooks. It is created during the setup process and generally shouldn''t be touched (except to make it read-only). the following constant variables are set in configure.php during the setup script:    HTTP_SERVER - Main webserver: eg, http://localhost - should not be empty for production servers   HTTPS_SERVER - Secure webserver: eg, https://localhost - should not be empty for production servers   ENABLE_SSL_ADMIN - secure webserver   DIR_WS_ADMIN - url path (these paths are relative to top of your webspace)   DIR_FS_ADMIN - The physical path is a COMPLETE path to your SmartBooks files.   DEFAULT_LANGUAGE - define the default language (can also be changed at login)    DB_TYPE - databse type (currently only mysql is supported)    DB_PREFIX - If smartbooks shares the database with other applications, a table prefix may be used.  &nbsp;');
