r screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Print a Label\r Labels can be printed manually through Shipping Manager or, for a particular invoice, through the Invoice Manager. If Invoice Manager is used, most of the information will be pre-entered into the label form. Verification of information and the package details are all that is needed. If a label is generated from Shipping Manager. the destination address must be entered and the package information.\r From Invoice Manager\r \r   Select Customers -&gt; Invoice Manager. Invoices are listed in descending order by invoice number.\r   Locate the invoice to generate a label from and press the Ship button. NOTE: Once a package has been shipped, the button will change to Void Shipment and the invoice cannot be re-shipped. \r   A popup form will appear with most of the fields filled in. The field information is derived from the invoice itself along with default values set in the Company -&gt; Shipping Defaults settings.\r   Enter the package weight, dimensions and insurance value. If more than one package is to be shipped with this invoice (Multi-piece), press the Plus sign to add another package row. \r   After all information has been entered, press the PDF icon and the label will be retrieved from UPS. \r   Once the label has been retrieved, the window will contain either a button to download the image (thermal printers) or a PDF image will appear in the window.\r   Print the label to the appropriate printer. NOTE: For thermal labels, the label must be printed in RAW format directly to the printer port. In this case, the label must be downloaded and saved locally, The file must then be copied (or moved) directly to the port the thermal printer is connected to. \r   Once all labels have been printed, close the label manager popup widow. \r \r From Shipping Manager\r \r   Select Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager.\r   Click on the Ship a Package button.\r   A popup form will appear with shipping default fields filled in. The field information is derived from the default values set in the Company -&gt; Shipping Defaults settings.\r   Enter the address information to ship the package. \r   Enter the package weight, dimensions and insurance value. If more than one package is to be shipped with this invoice (Multi-piece), press the Plus sign to add another package row. \r   After all information has been entered, press the PDF icon and the label will be retrieved from UPS. \r   Once the label has been retrieved, the window will contain either a button to download the image (thermal printers) or a PDF image will appear in the window.\r   Print the label to the appropriate printer. NOTE: For thermal labels, the label must be printed in RAW format directly to the printer port. In this case, the label must be downloaded and saved locally, The file must then be copied (or moved) directly to the port the thermal printer is connected to. \r   Once all labels have been printed, close the label manager popup widow.\r \r How to Re-Print a Label\r \r    From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the package to re-print the label. Click on the printer icon on the package line. NOTE: All labels are stored in the my_files directory on the server. re-printing will not re-query UPS but merely reload the image file from the original request. \r   Once the label has been retrieved (from your local my_files directory), the window will contain either a button to download the image (thermal printers) or a PDF image will appear in the window.\r   Print the label to the appropriate printer. NOTE: For thermal labels, the label must be printed in RAW format directly to the printer port. In this case, the label must be downloaded and saved locally, The file must then be copied (or moved) directly to the port the thermal printer is connected to. \r   Once all labels have been printed, close the label manager popup widow.\r \r How to Void a Shipment\r NOTE: Shipments can only be voided the same day the label was generated. \r \r   Packages can be deleted through either Invoice Manager or Ship Manager. \r   From Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to void the shipment. Press the Void Shipment button and a label void request will be sent to UPS. NOTE: Once a shipment is voided, the button from that invoice in Invoice Manager will revert back to the Ship state where the shipment can be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Shipping Manager, press the delete icon next to the package you want to void. Confirm the void operation and the shipment will be deleted. NOTE: UPS will only let an entire shipment be deleted, if the shipment contains more than one package, all packages in the shipment will be voided. \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track and click on the tracking number. \r   A new window will appear linked to the UPS.com web site and the tracking information will be automatically entered. \r   Packages can also be tracked through the Invoice Manager. Locate the invoice to track, select the View Ship Log icon and a popup will appear with the shipment information. The tracking number will appear in the log, Click on the tracking icon next to it to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r     Shipping Manager\r     Invoice Manger'),
(163, 159, 'd', 'en_us', '09.01.08', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/usps/USPSHome.html', 'Shipping Modules.USPS', 'Shipping Modules - United States Postal Service (USPS)', 'Shipping Modules - United States Postal Service (USPS)\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - United States Postal Service (USPS)\r \r SmartBooks includes a shipping module to calculate United States Postal Service (USPS) shipping charges. \r Features Include:\r \r   Freight quotes\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Vendor order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking information and shipping logs \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install USPS Shipping Module \r \r   Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the USPS row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r   Click on Install to install the USPS module. \r   Click the USPS row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Enter the rate information and press Save to save the changes. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Enter a Shipping Log Record\r \r    Shipping log entries are entered either through the Invoice Manager.\r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to create the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Ship button on the line the invoice appears.\r   A popup will appear with a form to enter the package information.\r   Select the Service Type, shipment/Expected receipt dates, tracking information and the shipment cost.\r   Press the Save icon to save the shipment information. NOTE: Once a shipment log entry has been generated, the button on Invoice Manager changes from Ship to Void Shipment.\r \r How to Void a Shipping Log Record\r \r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice you want to void the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Void Shipment button and the shipping log entry will be deleted. NOTE: The Invoice Manager will now allow the package to be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the shipment to void.\r   Press the Delete icon on the line of the shipment, confirm the void and the shipment record will be deleted. \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track. \r   Since USPS shipping is not tied to a particular vendor, only the tracking number will be displayed, it can now be copied to the clipboard and pasted into the carrier site to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r     Shipping Manager\r     Invoice Manger'),
(164, 159, 'd', 'en_us', '09.01.09', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/01-Modules/zone/ZoneHome.html', 'Shipping Modules.State/Province', 'Shipping Modules - Zone Rates (State/Province)', 'Shipping Modules - Zone Rates (State/Province)\r \r \r \r \r Shipping Modules - Zone Rates (State/Province)\r \r SmartBooks includes a shipping module to calculate zone based shipping charges. \r Features Include:\r \r   Freight quotes\r   Shipping Manager integration\r    Customer and Vendor order integration.\r   Integration with Invoice Manger \r   Tracking information and shipping logs \r   Report capability available through reportwriter. \r \r How to Install Zone Based Shipping Module \r \r   Through Setup -&gt; Shipping Settings, click on the Zone Based row in the table and a button labeled Install will appear on the right. \r   Click on Install to install the Zone Based module. \r   Click the Zone Based row again and Click on the Edit Button.\r   Enter the rate information and press Save to save the changes. \r \r Note: Place the sort order to a number greater than zero. IF THE SORT ORDER IS ZERO, IT WILL NOT SHOW UP. \r How the Get a Rate Quote\r \r   Rate quotes are available from the order screens. When shipping is enabled (Company -&gt; My Company -&gt; Enable Shipping Settings) a button will appear next to the freight method and price to load the shipping popup and request a rate. \r   The Shipping Quote popup will be mostly filled out with values pulled from the order and the shipping defaults. Changes , however can be made before the carrier servers are queried for rates.\r   Once the information in the shipping popup has been verified, Press the Next button and the rate estimator will pull the quoted rates form the selected services.\r   Click on the rate desired and the carrier, method, and rate information will be entered into the order form; the popup will close. \r \r Note: If the weight field of inventory items is filled out, the weight of the shipment will be automatically calculated and inserted into the rate estimator. \r How to Enter a Shipping Log Record\r \r    Shipping log entries are entered either through the Invoice Manager.\r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice to create the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Ship button on the line the invoice appears.\r   A popup will appear with a form to enter the package information.\r   Select the Service Type, shipment/Expected receipt dates, tracking information and the shipment cost.\r   Press the Save icon to save the shipment information. NOTE: Once a shipment log entry has been generated, the button on Invoice Manager changes from Ship to Void Shipment.\r \r How to Void a Shipping Log Record\r \r   From Customers -&gt; Invoice Manger, locate the invoice you want to void the shipping log entry.\r   Press the Void Shipment button and the shipping log entry will be deleted. NOTE: The Invoice Manager will now allow the package to be re-shipped if necessary.\r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, locate the shipment to void.\r   Press the Delete icon on the line of the shipment, confirm the void and the shipment record will be deleted. \r \r How to Track a Package\r \r   From Tools -&gt; Shipping Manager, select the date the package was shipped. Locate the package to track. \r   Since Zone Based shipping is not tied to a particular vendor, only the tracking number will be displayed, it can now be copied to the clipboard and pasted into the carrier site to track the package. \r \r Related Subjects\r How to Set up Shipping Defaults\r     Shipping Manager\r     Invoice Manger'),
(165, 167, 'd', 'en_us', '09.02', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/02-Installation/InstallationHome.html', 'Shipping Modules - Installation', 'Shipping Modules - Installation', 'Shipping Modules - Installation     Shipping Modules - Installation  Additional shipping modules can be downloaded from www.SmartBooks.com and installed into the /modules/shipping/directory. Please refer to the installation instructions included with each module for details installing the particular module.'),
(166, 167, 'd', 'en_us', '09.02', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/03-Removal/RemovalHome.html', 'Shipping Modules - Removal', 'Shipping Modules - Removal', 'Shipping Modules - Removal     Shipping Modules - Removal  There is no need to remove a particular shipping module. Simply uninstalling it will remove the module from appearing in any of SmartBooks functions.'),
(167, 0, '0', 'en_us', '09', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch09-Shipping/ShippingHome.html', 'Shipping', 'Shipping', 'Shipping\r \r \r \r \r Shipping\r \r SmartBooks contains powerful, flexible shipping tools to help estimate, ship, track and monitor your shipping needs. Several shipping modules are included with the standard distribution including FedEx, UPS and USPS along with non-carrier based shipping methods. \r Shipping Manager - The Shipping Manager tool is the main interface to the shipping functions. From here you can ship packages, track packages, review package volume and shipment costs and void shipments. \r Invoice Manager - The Invoice Manager includes a link to the shipping functions to allow for order fulfillment directly from the invoice. The invoice manager does most of the work for you by filling in the shipping form automatically. All you need to do i enter the package information and carrier approved label will be generated within SmartBooks.\r Related Links\r Shipping Modules\r   Invoice Manager\r  \r &nbsp;'),
(168, 0, 'd', 'en_us', '10', 'modules/smarterp/language/en_us/manual/ch10-ImportingExporting/ImpExpHome.html', 'Importing', 'Importing/Exporting', 'Importing/Exporting     Importing/Exporting SmartBooks has several ways to import data into the system.  With the exception of beginning balances, import operation are made through the Tools -&gt; Import/Export menu. Beginning balances are imported through the General Ledger -&gt; General Journal Utilities menu.  General Import Procedure     From the Tools -&gt; Import/Export menu, select the tab of the type of import you want to perform.   Scroll down the list and select the template to import from, press the Open icon.    The criteria tab will display the criteria for which to import data. This will allow filtering the imported data to only include the fields you are interested in.   Click on the fields tab. The table displayed lists the fields available to import. Column fields are defined as follows:            Sequence - Indicates the sequence the field appears in the import file format.       Field Name - This is a textual name for identifying the field to import. It is linked to the actual database field name.        Processing - Phreebooks allows for processing the data during the import operation. Imported values can be trimmed, formatted, etc. to meet the criteria of the database value ranges.        Import - Specifies whether the field is available for import. Generally, all fields are importable except the primary index field (usually named id)        Show - Indicates whether the field will be included in the import list or not. Yes = include, No = don''t include            Arrange the fields to match the sequence of the import data.   Save the import template for future use (it''s best to try a few trial runs to validate the import template before importing the entire data file.   Press the Options tab and select the delimiter and text qualifier for the import file. Check whether the first row contains header information. The header information is ignored during the import if checked, the import is sequence driven.     Press the Browse button and select the file to import.   Press the Import icon to initiate the import. NOTE: It''s best to try a smaller file at first on a test system until the import template is validated.  General Export Procedure Data can be exported using the same template as importing. The data file is downloaded to your browser and can be saved or viewed locally. Another option is to use the reportwriter tool to build the export data and select the csv option when creating the report.  Importing Contacts (Vendors/Customers/Employees)  Contacts can be imported into SmartBooks through csv or tab delimited format. Up to 5 of each billing and shipping addresses may be imported with each contact. Importing Inventory Inventory can be entered into SmartBooks as a csv or tab separated file. NOTE: make sure all additional inventory fields are set-up in the system before importing inventory. (See Inventory - Tabs and Fields)  Importing Beginning Balances Importing beginning balances is covered in the following section: Installation - Importing Beginning Balances  The following journals can be imported. Inventory, Purchase Orders, Purchase/receive Inventory, Sales Orders, Sales/Invoices. For inventory, the SKU''s must be present in the system prior to importing values. For the rest, the vendors/customers will be created during the import process, if necessary.  Importing Chart of Accounts &nbsp; Copying Companies  Companies can be copied to a new database along with selected information ranging from tables only to every record stored in the source company. Company operations are found in the Tools -&gt; Company Manager menu.');
